('The VectorStoreDocumentRetriever class retrieves documents from a vector store based on semantic similarity to a query, supporting filtering, similarity thresholds, and top-k results. It provides a builder pattern for configuration and allows for dynamic filter expressions.','This class interacts with a VectorStore interface to perform similarity searches. It\'s often used within Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) flows, potentially in conjunction with DocumentJoiners and ChatClients. It can be integrated with various vector database implementations like OpenSearch, Weaviate, and Redis.','org.springframework.ai.rag.retrieval.search.VectorStoreDocumentRetriever','```java\nVectorStoreDocumentRetriever retriever = VectorStoreDocumentRetriever.builder()\n    .vectorStore(vectorStore)\n    .similarityThreshold(0.73)\n    .topK(5)\n    .filterExpression(filterExpression)\n    .build();\nList<Document> documents = retriever.retrieve(new Query(\"example query\"));\n```\n\nOr, using a dynamic filter:\n\n```java\nVectorStoreDocumentRetriever retriever = VectorStoreDocumentRetriever.builder()\n    .vectorStore(vectorStore)\n    .filterExpression(() -> new FilterExpressionBuilder()\n        .eq(\"tenant\", TenantContextHolder.getTenantIdentifier())\n        .build())\n    .build();\nList<Document> documents = retriever.retrieve(new Query(\"What are the KPIs for the next semester?\"));\n```','d8cd482d-c215-4d8e-955c-00cd78c9c152'),
('The `QueryAugmenter` interface defines a functional component for enriching a user query with contextual data retrieved from documents. This is crucial for providing large language models with the necessary information to generate informed responses.','This interface is a core component within the Spring AI `spring-ai-rag` module, specifically used in conjunction with `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor`, `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever`, and `ContextualQueryAugmenter`. It\'s part of the RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) pipeline, enabling the injection of relevant context into prompts before they are sent to a language model. It extends the `BiFunction` interface, making it easily composable with other functional components.','org.springframework.ai.rag.generation.augmentation.QueryAugmenter','Implementations like `ContextualQueryAugmenter` are used to augment queries. The `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` utilizes a `QueryAugmenter` to enhance the user\'s query with data retrieved from a `VectorStore`. You can customize the augmentation process by providing your own `QueryAugmenter` implementation or configuring options like `allowEmptyContext` in `ContextualQueryAugmenter` to control behavior when no relevant documents are found.','c0998010-3804-4cad-9e47-0170c2a7b9c4'),
('AbstractFilterExpressionConverter is an abstract class providing a base implementation for converting Filter.Expression objects into string representations. It handles different operand types (Group, Key, Value, Expression) and delegates the actual conversion of each type to abstract methods that subclasses must implement.','This class serves as a base class for concrete filter expression converters. It\'s part of a filter expression conversion system, likely used to translate filter criteria into a string format suitable for querying or other operations. It interacts with the Filter interface and its related classes (Expression, Operand, Group, Key, Value).','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.converter.AbstractFilterExpressionConverter','Extend this class to create specific filter expression converters. Implement the `doExpression`, `doKey` methods to define how expressions and keys are converted to strings. Use the provided methods (e.g., `convertOperand`, `doValue`, `doGroup`) to handle common operand types and build the string representation recursively. Ensure that non-AND/OR expressions have a Value as the right argument to avoid runtime exceptions.','4b086d9a-936e-4cb6-b75d-03d154ac4b42'),
('The `DocumentJoiner` interface defines a component for combining lists of documents retrieved from multiple queries and data sources into a single list. It provides a `join` method to perform this combination, potentially handling duplicates and reciprocal ranking.','This interface is used in Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) pipelines to consolidate documents from various sources (e.g., vector stores, search engines) before feeding them to a language model. It works with classes like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` to retrieve documents and potentially with components like `RagService` to generate responses based on the combined documents. Implementations like `ConcatenationDocumentJoiner` provide specific joining strategies.','org.springframework.ai.rag.retrieval.join.DocumentJoiner','Implementations of `DocumentJoiner` are used to combine the results of multiple document retrievals. For example, a `ConcatenationDocumentJoiner` can be used to simply concatenate the lists of documents, while more sophisticated implementations might apply deduplication or ranking strategies. The interface is functional, allowing for lambda expressions or method references to be used for joining.','99d38a42-eccf-410d-9fe4-0a9ad93ba57d'),
('This enum, `Operation`, defines the possible operations that can be performed on a VectorStore: adding data, deleting data, and performing similarity queries.','This enum is used within the `VectorStore` interface and related components (like `CosmosDBVectorStore`) to categorize and track operations for observability purposes, providing metrics and tracing data via Micrometer. It\'s also related to observability features for other components like `ChatModel` and `EmbeddingModel`.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.Operation','Use this enum when defining or logging VectorStore operations. For example, when recording metrics or tracing information, use `Operation.ADD`, `Operation.DELETE`, or `Operation.QUERY` to specify the type of operation being performed. The `value()` method can be used to retrieve the string representation of the operation.','df99a277-49ca-45f0-ba53-0aa45762c7cd'),
('This class, `DefaultVectorStoreObservationConvention`, provides default conventions for populating observations when interacting with vector stores. It defines how to name observations, generate contextual names based on the database system and operation, and create key-value pairs for low and high cardinality data. These key-value pairs are used for metrics and tracing in observability systems.','This class is part of the Spring AI observability framework and is used by `VectorStore` implementations to generate metrics and traces. It works with `VectorStoreObservationContext` to gather information about the vector store operation and uses `KeyValues` and `KeyValue` to structure the observation data. It integrates with Micrometer for exporting metrics and tracing data.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.DefaultVectorStoreObservationConvention','To use this class, you typically don\'t need to instantiate it directly. Spring AI automatically uses it (or a custom implementation) when interacting with vector stores if observability is enabled. You can customize the observation name by providing a custom name to the constructor. Ensure Spring Boot Actuator is included in your project to enable observability features. The documentation shows how to set up a `CosmosDBVectorStore` which will utilize this convention for observation data.','6337e358-11b1-487a-8362-0bca33ca7c36'),
('This enum defines a set of key names used for high-cardinality attributes in vector store operations, primarily for observability purposes. These keys are used to tag metrics and traces related to database interactions, similarity searches, and vector data within a vector store.','This enum is closely related to the observability features of Spring AI, specifically Micrometer and tracing. It provides standardized keys for adding context to metrics and traces generated by `VectorStore` implementations and related components like `ChatClient` and `ChatModel`. It also interacts with `VectorStoreObservationAttributes` to retrieve the actual attribute values.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.HighCardinalityKeyNames','Use these keys when instrumenting vector store operations to provide detailed observability data. For example, when logging the time taken for a similarity search, include the `DB_COLLECTION_NAME`, `DB_SEARCH_SIMILARITY_METRIC`, and `DB_VECTOR_QUERY_TOP_K` keys to provide context about the search parameters. The documentation shows how to set up `CosmosDBVectorStore` and add/search documents, which would utilize these keys for observation.','a5cb84a6-fdf7-4ea0-91ef-0e12cabf32a1'),
('The `CompareContext` class represents the context for comparison operations within a filter expression. It provides access to tokens representing comparison operators like equals, greater than, less than, etc.','This class is part of the ANTLR4-based parser generated for the filter expression DSL. It\'s used by the `FiltersParser` and interacted with by listeners (`FiltersListener`) and visitors (`FiltersVisitor`) during the parsing process. It\'s related to `Filter.Expression` as it helps parse the comparison part of the expression string (e.g., `country == \'UK\'`).','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.CompareContext','This class is not directly instantiated or used by application code. It\'s an internal component of the parser. Its methods (e.g., `EQUALS()`, `GT()`) are used by the parser to identify and access the comparison operators within a filter expression string.  For example, a listener might use `EQUALS()` to determine if an equals comparison is present in the parsed expression.','09df7e1e-5cf3-48fa-aa17-0f997fbea693'),
('The `SearchRequest` class represents a request for similarity search operations. It encapsulates the query text, the desired number of results (`topK`), a similarity threshold, and an optional filter expression for metadata filtering.','This class is a core component for interacting with vector stores (like PgVector, OracleVectorStore, CosmosDBVectorStore, Milvus, Pinecone, CassandraVectorStore, ChromaVector store) within the Spring AI framework. It\'s used as input to the `similaritySearch` method of `VectorStoreRetriever` and `VectorStore` interfaces. It also relates to `Filter.Expression`, `FilterExpressionBuilder`, and `FilterExpressionTextParser` for defining metadata filters.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.SearchRequest','1. **Basic Search:** Create a `SearchRequest` using the builder to specify the query and desired number of results:\\n\\n   ```java\\n   List<Document> results = vectorStore.similaritySearch(SearchRequest.builder().query(\\\"Spring AI\\\").topK(5).build());\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Filtering:** Add metadata filters using `filterExpression` with either a text expression or a `Filter.Expression` object:\\n\\n   ```java\\n   List<Document> results = vectorStore.similaritySearch(SearchRequest.builder().query(\\\"The World\\\").topK(TOP_K).filterExpression(\\\"author in [\'john\', \'jill\'] && article_type == \'blog\'\").build());\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Similarity Threshold:** Control the minimum similarity score for returned results:\\n\\n   ```java\\n   List<Document> results = vectorStore.similaritySearch(SearchRequest.builder().query(\\\"Spring AI\\\").topK(5).similarityThreshold(0.8).build());\\n   ```','5cb7c6db-68fc-4d5e-8ed8-119672ea2f53'),
('The `Builder` interface defines a fluent API for constructing `VectorStore` instances. It allows configuring observation settings (registry and convention), batching strategy, and ultimately building the `VectorStore` object.','This interface is used by concrete `VectorStore` implementations (e.g., `MariaDBVectorStore`, `TypesenseVectorStore`, `CosmosDBVectorStore`) to provide a configurable construction process. It\'s part of the Spring AI vector store abstraction, working alongside interfaces like `VectorStore` and `SearchRequest`.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.Builder','The `Builder` pattern is used to create and configure `VectorStore` instances.  For example, when configuring `MariaDBVectorStore`, the builder allows setting options like dimensions, distance type, schema name, and table names. Similarly, `TypesenseVectorStore` uses the builder to configure collection name, embedding dimension, and batching strategy.','e592adc7-bc45-4af8-9aeb-1293e78d0dcb'),
('The FilterHelper class provides static methods for transforming and manipulating filter expressions. It offers functionality to negate expressions (e.g., converting AND to OR, EQ to NE) and expand IN/NIN expressions into equivalent expressions using OR/AND and EQ/NE operators, respectively. This is particularly useful for vector stores that may not natively support all filter expression types.','This class is a utility class used in conjunction with the `Filter` class and related components like `FilterExpressionConverter` and `SearchRequest`. It\'s designed to support filter expression manipulation within a vector database context, interacting with classes like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` and potentially other vector store implementations. It also interacts with the `FilterExpressionBuilder` for programmatic filter creation.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterHelper','1. **Negating Filters:** Use `FilterHelper.negate(operand)` to invert a filter expression. This is useful for implementing \'NOT\' conditions. 2. **Expanding IN/NIN:** Use `FilterHelper.expandIn(expression, context, converter)` or `FilterHelper.expandNin(expression, context, converter)` to convert IN/NIN expressions into equivalent expressions using OR/AND and EQ/NE, which can be necessary for vector stores with limited native support.  3. **Building Filters:** Combine `FilterHelper` with `FilterExpressionBuilder` to create complex filter expressions programmatically.','5cece3bd-31da-4e6c-8df5-1586f72e3482'),
('This class is a Builder for creating instances of `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever`. It allows configuring the retriever with a `VectorStore`, a similarity threshold, the number of top results to retrieve (`topK`), and an optional filter expression.','The `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` likely interacts with a `VectorStore` interface to perform similarity searches. It also uses `Filter.Expression` to filter search results. It\'s part of a retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) system, potentially used within a larger chat or question-answering application.','org.springframework.ai.rag.retrieval.search.Builder','To use the builder, first obtain an instance (typically through `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever.builder()`). Then, chain calls to `vectorStore()`, `similarityThreshold()`, `topK()`, and `filterExpression()` to configure the retriever. Finally, call `build()` to create the `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` instance. For example:\n\n```java\nVectorStoreDocumentRetriever retriever = VectorStoreDocumentRetriever.builder()\n    .vectorStore(myVectorStore)\n    .similarityThreshold(0.8)\n    .topK(5)\n    .filterExpression(myFilterExpression)\n    .build();\n```','3b5863d2-0df1-4aab-8d64-1919bfa0cc5d'),
('This class contains integration tests for a `PineconeFilterExpressionConverter` which converts a structured expression (using `EQ`, `AND`, `IN`, etc.) into a Pinecone-compatible vector expression represented as a JSON string. The tests cover various combinations of expressions, including equality, greater than/less than, \'in\' operator, logical AND/OR, grouping, and different data types (strings, numbers, booleans).','This class tests the `PineconeFilterExpressionConverter` class, which is likely responsible for translating filter criteria into a format suitable for querying a Pinecone vector database. It interacts with custom classes like `Expression`, `Key`, and `Value` which define the structure of the filter expression before conversion. It doesn\'t appear to have direct relationships with other major components beyond these.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.converter.PineconeFilterExpressionConverterTests','The primary use case is to verify the correct conversion of complex filter expressions into the JSON format expected by Pinecone.  Key examples include:\n\n1.  **Simple Equality:** `testEQ()` demonstrates converting `country == \"BG\"` to `{\"country\": {\"$eq\": \"BG\"}}`.\n2.  **Combined Conditions:** `tesEqAndGte()` shows how `genre == \"drama\" AND year >= 2020` is converted to `{\"$and\": [{\"genre\": {\"$eq\": \"drama\"}},{\"year\": {\"$gte\": 2020}}]}`, illustrating the handling of logical AND.\n3.  **\'In\' Operator:** `tesIn()` demonstrates converting `genre in [\"comedy\", \"documentary\", \"drama\"]` to `{\"genre\": {\"$in\": [\"comedy\",\"documentary\",\"drama\"]}}`.\n4.  **Complex Nesting:** `testComplexAndOrCombination()` and `testNestedGroups()` showcase the conversion of deeply nested AND/OR expressions with grouping.','612d75a2-6a83-4348-a8b6-199342ead270'),
('The FilterExpressionBuilder class provides a fluent DSL for constructing filter expressions used for querying data, particularly within vector stores. It allows building complex boolean expressions with various operators like equals, not equals, greater than, less than, in, and not in, combined with AND and OR logic.','This class is closely related to the Filter.Expression class, as it\'s a builder for creating instances of it. It\'s also used in conjunction with various vector store implementations (PgVector, OracleVectorStore, Milvus, ChromaVectorStore, Typesense, AzureVectorStore, Couchbase, Elasticsearch) to filter search results based on metadata. It\'s used by components like VectorStoreDocumentRetriever to construct filter expressions for querying vector stores.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterExpressionBuilder','To use the builder, start with `new FilterExpressionBuilder()`. Then, chain methods like `eq()`, `ne()`, `gt()`, `gte()`, `lt()`, `lte()`, `in()`, `nin()`, `and()`, `or()`, and `group()` to construct the desired filter expression. Finally, call `build()` on the resulting `Op` object to obtain a `Filter.Expression` instance. For example: `b.and(b.eq(\"genre\", \"drama\"), b.gte(\"year\", 2020)).build()`','5df8b30c-81b8-46ef-873d-19c9e3465977'),
('This class is a builder for creating `SimpleVectorStore` instances. It extends `AbstractVectorStoreBuilder` and requires an `EmbeddingModel` to be initialized.','This builder is directly related to the `SimpleVectorStore` class, which it instantiates. It also relies on an `EmbeddingModel` for generating embeddings. It\'s part of a larger system of vector stores and embedding models within the Spring AI framework.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.SimpleVectorStoreBuilder','The `SimpleVectorStoreBuilder` is used to create a `SimpleVectorStore` instance.  First, an instance of the builder is created with an `EmbeddingModel`. Then, the `build()` method is called to create the `SimpleVectorStore`.','a1d7976b-90a5-4edf-81c1-1c4933c50630'),
('The `VectorStoreObservationContext` class is designed to store metadata related to vector store operations, facilitating observability and tracing within a Spring AI application. It extends `Observation.Context` to provide a structured way to capture details about interactions with vector stores.','This class is used in conjunction with Spring AI\'s `VectorStore` interface and related components (like `ChatClient`, `ChatMemory`, and `VectorStoreChatMemoryAdvisor`) to provide observability data. It integrates with Micrometer for metrics and tracing, and is particularly relevant when using Spring Boot Actuator for monitoring. It\'s also used with `SearchRequest` and `Document` classes to capture query and response details.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.VectorStoreObservationContext','To use this class, typically you\'d leverage its `Builder` to create an instance with relevant information before or during a vector store operation. For example:\n```java\nVectorStoreObservationContext context = VectorStoreObservationContext.builder(\"CosmosDB\", VectorStoreObservationContext.Operation.QUERY)\n    .collectionName(\"myCollection\")\n    .queryRequest(searchRequest)\n    .build();\n```\nThis context can then be used to enrich logging or tracing information associated with the vector store interaction.','fbef158c-ce02-4e88-b420-1e6825f863d0'),
('Represents the context for a comparison expression within a filter expression used for similarity searches in a vector database. It provides access to the identifier, comparison operator, and constant value involved in the comparison.','This class is part of the ANTLR4-based DSL used to construct `Filter.Expression` objects, which are then used as parameters in the `similaritySearch` methods of a vector database interface. It interacts with `FiltersListener` and `FiltersVisitor` for parsing and evaluation.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.CompareExpressionContext','This class is primarily used internally by the filter expression parser.  Users don\'t directly instantiate it. Instead, they define filter expressions as strings (e.g., `country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020 && isActive == true`) which are then parsed into a tree of contexts like `CompareExpressionContext` to evaluate the filter conditions.','1cffb9fb-8bbf-4a7b-9281-1f3c33978bd0'),
('This class, `LongConstantContext`, is a parser context representing a long integer constant within a filter expression. It extends `ConstantContext` and provides access to the tokens that make up the constant, such as the integer value, optional long suffix, and optional plus or minus sign.','This class is part of the ANTLR4-generated parser for filter expressions used with the vector database\'s `similaritySearch` methods. It\'s related to `ConstantContext`, `FiltersListener`, and `FiltersVisitor` interfaces, and is used to represent a specific type of constant (long integer) within a larger filter expression defined by `Filter.Expression`.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.LongConstantContext','This class is not directly instantiated by the user. It\'s an internal component of the filter expression parsing process. It\'s used by the parser to represent and navigate the structure of a long integer constant within a filter string like `year >= 2020`. The `INTEGER_VALUE()`, `LONG_SUFFIX()`, `MINUS()`, and `PLUS()` methods are used to access the individual tokens that comprise the constant.','d0b1e1b0-13d2-4873-945d-20bf395c8ff5'),
('The `QueryTransformer` interface defines a component for modifying input queries to improve retrieval effectiveness. It addresses issues like poorly formed queries, ambiguous terms, and unsupported languages. It functions as a functional interface, accepting a `Query` object and returning a transformed `Query` object.','This interface is a key component in Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) pipelines, specifically within the pre-retrieval phase. It works alongside components like `ChatClient`, `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever`, `DocumentPostProcessor`, and various transformer implementations (e.g., `CompressionQueryTransformer`, `RewriteQueryTransformer`, `TranslationQueryTransformer`, `MultiQueryExpander`) to prepare queries for optimal vector database searching. It\'s also related to the broader ETL pipeline concept.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.transformation.QueryTransformer','Implementations of `QueryTransformer` are used to preprocess user queries before they are sent to a vector database.  For example, `CompressionQueryTransformer` can condense long conversation histories into a single query.  `RewriteQueryTransformer` can rephrase queries for better search results.  When using `QueryTransformer` with a `ChatClient`, setting a low temperature (e.g., 0.0) is recommended for more deterministic and accurate results.','a2906bd2-0ec2-4e6b-9667-215e55e628d1'),
('This class contains unit tests for the `DefaultVectorStoreObservationConvention`. It verifies the convention\'s name, contextual name generation, context support (specifically for `VectorStoreObservationContext`), and the key values (both low and high cardinality) it produces based on the provided context. It also checks that key values are not generated when context data is missing.','This class is a testing component for `DefaultVectorStoreObservationConvention`, which is part of the Spring AI observability features. It interacts with `VectorStoreObservationContext`, `Observation`, `KeyValue`, `LowCardinalityKeyNames`, `SpringAiKind`, `HighCardinalityKeyNames`, `SearchRequest`, and `Document` to validate the observation convention\'s behavior. It\'s related to the broader Spring AI project\'s effort to provide metrics and tracing for AI operations, particularly those involving vector stores.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.DefaultVectorStoreObservationConventionTests','The primary use of this class is for internal testing and quality assurance of the `DefaultVectorStoreObservationConvention`. It demonstrates how to verify the correct generation of observation data for vector store interactions.  A key example is building a `VectorStoreObservationContext` with various parameters and asserting the expected `KeyValue` pairs are generated for both low and high cardinality metrics. This ensures that the observability features accurately capture relevant information about vector store operations.','24dc549c-6c2c-4ad5-acbc-2276b08cce55'),
('This class is a custom exception, `FilterExpressionParseException`, extending `RuntimeException`. It\'s designed to signal errors that occur during the parsing of filter expressions, likely used for querying or filtering data.','This exception is used in conjunction with components that handle filter expressions, such as `FilterExpressionBuilder`, `Filter.Expression`, `FilterExpressionTextParser`, and `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever`. It\'s part of the filtering mechanism used in vector stores to refine search results based on metadata. It is also used within the `SearchRequest` class when parsing filter expressions.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterExpressionParseException','This exception is thrown when a filter expression is invalid or cannot be parsed correctly. It\'s typically caught to handle errors related to user-provided filter strings or issues within the filter expression parsing logic. It is used to signal issues when constructing `Filter.Expression` objects, either from text or programmatically.','af52dfc7-47b4-413f-a61b-27a0838c6278'),
('Represents the \'and\' expression context within a boolean expression filter. This class is part of the parser generated code for handling filter expressions.','This class is a component of a larger filter expression system, likely used to parse and evaluate filter conditions for similarity searches in a vector database. It relates to `BooleanExpressionContext`, `FiltersParser`, `FiltersListener`, and `FiltersVisitor`. It\'s used in conjunction with `Filter.Expression` to define metadata filters for document retrieval.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.AndExpressionContext','This class is primarily used internally by the parser and visitor patterns generated by ANTLR4. It\'s not directly instantiated in application code. Instead, it\'s a node in the parse tree representing a logical AND operation between two boolean expressions. Example: `country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020 && isActive == true` would be parsed into a tree containing instances of this class.','f62de38e-57e8-43e2-be88-29baf672eae8'),
('This class is a Builder for creating `Query` objects. It allows setting the query text, history of messages, and context data in a fluent manner.','The `Builder` class is an inner static class of the `Query` class. It\'s used to construct `Query` instances with various parameters. It is related to classes like `Message`, `Filter`, `FilterExpressionBuilder`, `SearchRequest` and `VectorStore` as it is used to construct queries for vector search operations.','org.springframework.ai.rag.Builder','To create a `Query` object, use the `Builder` class\'s methods to set the desired parameters and then call the `build()` method. For example:\n\n```java\nQuery query = Query.Builder()\n    .text(\"Your query text\")\n    .history(List.of(new Message(\"User\", \"First message\")))\n    .context(Map.of(\"key\", \"value\"))\n    .build();\n```','75dd425f-451c-4510-a8d9-2c5e17702bc8'),
('The `ContextualQueryAugmenter` class augments a user\'s query with contextual data retrieved from a list of documents. It uses prompt templates to format the query and context for a language model, and handles cases where no context is available, either by returning a specific message or the original query based on configuration.','This class is a core component within the Spring AI framework, specifically used in Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) pipelines. It works in conjunction with `Query`, `Document`, `PromptTemplate`, and `QueryAugmenter` interfaces. It\'s often used as part of an `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` to enhance the `ChatClient`\'s ability to answer questions based on provided knowledge sources.','org.springframework.ai.rag.generation.augmentation.ContextualQueryAugmenter','The primary use case is to enhance a user query with relevant context before sending it to a language model.  A typical example involves building an instance using the builder pattern:\n\n```java\nQueryAugmenter augmenter = ContextualQueryAugmenter.builder()\n   .allowEmptyContext(false)\n   .build();\nQuery augmentedQuery = augmenter.augment(query, documents);\n```\n\nThis allows customization of prompt templates and handling of empty context scenarios. The `allowEmptyContext` flag controls whether the model should attempt to answer without context or return a \'don\'t know\' response.','43ab228f-ea35-449e-8e43-306efb032fb3'),
('This class is a Builder for creating `SearchRequest` objects. It allows setting the query, top K results, and similarity threshold for a similarity search.','This class is closely related to `SearchRequest`, `Filter.Expression`, `FilterExpressionTextParser`, and `FilterExpressionBuilder`. It\'s used to construct `SearchRequest` objects which are then used to perform similarity searches against a vector store. It leverages `Filter.Expression` for metadata filtering, and `FilterExpressionTextParser` and `FilterExpressionBuilder` to create these expressions.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.Builder','To use the builder, chain the desired methods (query, topK, similarityThreshold, filterExpression) and then call the build() method. For example:\n\n```java\nSearchRequest request = SearchRequest.Builder()\n    .query(\"example query\")\n    .topK(10)\n    .similarityThreshold(0.8)\n    .filterExpression(\"metadata_key == \'value\'\")\n    .build();\n```','f17d8383-4f4c-42cf-a6a5-325157f8c57e'),
('The `Query` record represents a query within a Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) flow. It encapsulates the query text, conversation history, and any relevant context data. It ensures data integrity through validation of input parameters.','This class is a core component in RAG applications, likely used as input to a `ChatClient` or similar component for generating responses. It interacts with components like `Message` (for history) and potentially `VectorStoreRetriever` to retrieve context. It\'s a data transfer object representing the complete query state.','org.springframework.ai.rag.Query','Create a `Query` instance to represent a user\'s request with its context. Use the builder for flexible construction, especially when adding history or context incrementally.  For simple queries without history or context, use the single-argument constructor.  The `mutate()` method allows for creating a modified copy of an existing `Query`.','fb8e01a6-c17d-4d27-aa3f-3556b87b33ed'),
('This class `SimpleVectorStoreWithFilterTests` contains integration tests for the `SimpleVectorStore` class, focusing on adding documents and performing similarity searches with various filter expressions. It mocks an `EmbeddingModel` to provide consistent embeddings for testing purposes.','This class tests `SimpleVectorStore`, which is likely a component responsible for storing and retrieving vector embeddings of documents. It interacts with a mocked `EmbeddingModel` to generate these embeddings. The tests demonstrate how filtering capabilities integrate with the vector store\'s search functionality. It also relates to `Document` and `SearchRequest` classes.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.SimpleVectorStoreWithFilterTests','The primary use case demonstrated is adding documents with metadata and then querying them using similarity search with filter expressions. Filters can be based on equality (e.g., `country == \'BG\'`), \'in\' conditions (e.g., `country in [\'BG\', \'NL\']`), range conditions (e.g., `value >= 1 && value <= 1`), and boolean values. The tests cover scenarios with single and multiple documents, ensuring correct results are returned based on the applied filters.','fe22afbc-9fdd-4ff4-81a7-379d99335844'),
('Represents the \'or\' expression context within a filter expression, as defined by the ANTLR4 grammar for filters. It holds references to the left and right boolean expression contexts and the \'OR\' token.','This class is part of a parser generated by ANTLR4, specifically for handling filter expressions. It\'s related to `BooleanExpressionContext`, `FiltersParser`, `FiltersListener`, and `FiltersVisitor`. It\'s used to represent a logical OR operation within a larger filter expression, which is used to filter documents based on their metadata during similarity searches.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.OrExpressionContext','This class is primarily used internally by the filter expression parser. Users don\'t directly instantiate it. Instead, they provide a filter expression string (e.g., `country == \'UK\' || year > 2020`) which is then parsed into a tree of contexts, including `OrExpressionContext`, to represent the expression\'s structure. The `Filter.Expression` class utilizes this parser to evaluate the filter string.','012bd165-0ba7-4d4e-a0aa-3a4d26090426'),
('Represents the \'in\' expression context within a filter expression, used for similarity searches in a vector database. It parses and holds information about an \'IN\' operator and its associated values.','This class is part of the ANTLR4-based filter expression DSL. It extends `BooleanExpressionContext` and is used by the `FiltersParser` and related listener/visitor interfaces (`FiltersListener`, `FiltersVisitor`). It\'s used in conjunction with `Filter.Expression` to define metadata filters for document retrieval.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.InExpressionContext','This class is not directly instantiated but is a result of parsing a filter expression string like `country IN (\'UK\', \'USA\')`. The `identifier()` method retrieves the metadata key (e.g., \'country\'), `IN()` retrieves the \'IN\' token, and `constantArray()` retrieves the array of values to check against.','ec8ce10a-7052-4356-8479-3c9762896baf'),
('This class, `VectorStoreRuntimeHints`, is a `RuntimeHintsRegistrar` implementation that registers resources needed at runtime, specifically the ANTLR4 grammar file for filtering in vector stores.','This class is part of the Spring AI project and likely interacts with the vector store components, particularly those related to filtering. It contributes to the AOT (Ahead-Of-Time) compilation process by ensuring necessary resources are included.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.aot.VectorStoreRuntimeHints','This class is automatically used during the application startup process when AOT compilation is enabled. No direct instantiation or method calls are typically required. It ensures that the `Filters.g4` resource is available at runtime for the vector store filtering functionality.','0b1bab2d-0bd7-4063-b6fe-3cbb54e28cea'),
('Represents a \'NIN\' (Not IN) expression within a filter expression used for similarity searches in a vector database. It parses and holds information about the \'NIN\' operator, identifiers, constant arrays, and negation.','This class is part of the filter expression DSL (Domain-Specific Language) used with the `similaritySearch` methods of a vector database interface. It works in conjunction with other expression contexts (like `BooleanExpressionContext`, `IdentifierContext`, `ConstantArrayContext`) and is processed by `FiltersListener` and `FiltersVisitor` during parsing and evaluation. It\'s used to filter `Document` metadata based on whether a value is *not* present in a given set.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.NinExpressionContext','This class is primarily used internally by the ANTLR4-based parser generated from the `FiltersParser`.  Developers typically interact with it indirectly by constructing filter expressions as strings (e.g., `country NIN (\'USA\', \'Canada\')`) which are then parsed into a tree of contexts like `NinExpressionContext`.  The `enterRule`, `exitRule`, and `accept` methods facilitate traversal and processing of the parse tree by listeners and visitors.','679281e0-0531-49ed-bbe1-3e3787d44906'),
('The `Op` record class is a wrapper around a `Filter.Expression` that simplifies its usage by automatically unwrapping nested `Filter.Group` expressions. It ensures that the returned `Filter.Expression` is not a group, providing a cleaner interface for filter operations.','This class is closely related to `Filter.Expression` and `Filter.Group`. It\'s used to process and simplify `Filter.Expression` objects, particularly when dealing with potentially nested groups. It is used within components like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` and `SearchRequest` to handle metadata filtering.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.Op','The primary use case is to ensure a `Filter.Expression` is not wrapped in a `Filter.Group`.  For example:\n\n```java\nOp op = new Op(new Filter.Group(new Filter.Expression()));\nFilter.Expression expression = op.build(); // expression will be the inner Filter.Expression\n```\n\nOr:\n\n```java\nOp op = new Op(new Filter.Expression());\nFilter.Expression expression = op.build(); // expression will be the original Filter.Expression\n```','5a4c1760-98bd-41cc-b6fc-3fca7d39490d'),
('The `VectorStoreRetriever` interface provides read-only access to vector store retrieval operations, allowing you to search for documents based on similarity to a query. It\'s a functional interface designed for scenarios where only retrieval is needed, adhering to the principle of least privilege.','This interface is a read-only counterpart to the `VectorStore` interface, which includes both read and write operations. `VectorStore` extends `VectorStoreRetriever`. It\'s often used in RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) applications with components like `ChatModel` and can be implemented by concrete vector store implementations like `MongoDBAtlasVectorStore`.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.VectorStoreRetriever','The primary use case is retrieving documents using `similaritySearch()`. You can either provide a simple query string or a `SearchRequest` object with more specific parameters like `topK` and `similarityThreshold`.  For example:\n\n1.  Basic search: `retriever.similaritySearch(\"user query\")`\n2.  Advanced search: `retriever.similaritySearch(SearchRequest.builder().query(\"query\").topK(5).build())`\n3.  Using in a RAG service: Retrieve relevant documents and use them as context for a language model.','ba9e70ff-33cf-427f-a51a-403f3dc1ece3'),
('This enum, `VectorStoreObservationDocumentation`, defines documentation conventions for observations related to vector stores. It provides a centralized way to manage key names (attributes) used for metrics and tracing when interacting with vector stores. It differentiates between low-cardinality and high-cardinality key names, impacting how they are used in observability data. The `AI_VECTOR_STORE` member is the primary entry point for accessing these conventions.','This class is part of the Spring AI observability framework and is used to standardize observation attributes for vector store interactions. It integrates with Micrometer for metrics and tracing, and is used by components like `VectorStore` to emit observability data. It relates to other observability components within Spring AI and the Spring ecosystem (e.g., Spring Boot Actuator).','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.VectorStoreObservationDocumentation','To leverage these observations, ensure the Spring Boot Actuator dependency is included in your project. The `VectorStore` implementations in Spring AI are automatically instrumented to use these conventions. No explicit configuration is typically needed, but you can customize observation settings through Spring Boot properties (e.g., to control which attributes are logged or traced). The example in the documentation shows how to use a `VectorStore` for similarity search and demonstrates basic operations like adding and deleting documents.','222a1923-fff9-4641-83a6-4250be4f8f3e'),
('This class, `DecimalConstantContext`, represents the context for a decimal constant within a filter expression defined by the `FiltersParser`. It provides access to the tokens representing the decimal value, plus or minus sign.','This class is part of an ANTLR4-generated parser structure for filter expressions. It extends `ConstantContext` and is used by `FiltersListener` and `FiltersVisitor` to process decimal constants within a larger filter expression. It\'s related to the `Filter.Expression` class mentioned in the documentation, as it helps parse the string representation of filter expressions.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.DecimalConstantContext','This class is not directly instantiated or used by application code. It\'s an internal component of the filter parsing process. The documentation highlights how filter expressions (which this class helps parse) are used with `similaritySearch` methods to filter documents based on metadata.','128a9ab2-0eec-4839-a61e-4372ac7fbb62'),
('This class, `TextConstantContext`, is a context object generated by ANTLR4, representing a text constant within a parsed filter expression. It provides access to the tokens representing quoted strings.','This class is part of the ANTLR4-generated parser infrastructure for filter expressions. It\'s related to `ConstantContext`, `FiltersParser`, `FiltersListener`, and `FiltersVisitor`. It facilitates navigating and processing the parse tree of a filter expression, specifically focusing on text constants.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.TextConstantContext','This class is primarily used within the parsing and evaluation of filter expressions.  It allows access to the quoted string tokens within the expression.  Listeners and visitors can use the `enterTextConstant`, `exitTextConstant`, and `visitTextConstant` methods to process these constants during parsing.','6209d5be-43ca-463a-9aee-44c230918ec7'),
('The `VectorStore` interface defines operations for managing and querying documents in a vector database. It extends `DocumentWriter` and `VectorStoreRetriever`, providing methods for adding, deleting, and searching documents based on vector similarity. It also includes a builder interface for configuring observation-related settings.','This interface is central to Spring AI\'s vector database integration. Implementations like `MongoDBAtlasVectorStore`, `MariaDBVectorStore`, `OpenSearchVectorStore`, `WeaviateVectorStore`, `RedisVectorStore`, and `PineconeVectorStore` provide concrete connections to different vector database systems. It works with `Document` objects and utilizes `EmbeddingModel` for vector representation. It\'s used in conjunction with `Filter` for targeted deletions and `SearchRequest` for similarity searches.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.VectorStore','1. **Adding Documents:** Use `add(List<Document> documents)` to store documents in the vector store.\n2. **Deleting Documents:** Use `delete(List<String> idList)` to delete by ID or `delete(String filterExpression)` to delete based on a filter.\n3. **Similarity Search:** Implementations of `VectorStoreRetriever` (which this interface extends) are used for similarity searches.\n4. **Builder Pattern:** Utilize the `Builder` interface to configure the vector store with settings like observation registry and batching strategy.','3f285ddc-df96-48b3-845a-44f3f976bfa6'),
('The `CompressionQueryTransformer` compresses a conversation history and a follow-up query into a standalone query using a large language model. This is useful for long conversation histories where the follow-up query relies on context from the history.','This class is a `QueryTransformer` used in a Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline, specifically in the pre-retrieval phase to improve query effectiveness. It interacts with a `ChatClient` to generate the compressed query and utilizes `PromptTemplate` for customizable prompts. It\'s part of a larger ETL pipeline for preparing data for AI models.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.transformation.CompressionQueryTransformer','To use the `CompressionQueryTransformer`, first build an instance using the `builder()` method, providing a `ChatClient.Builder`.  Then, call the `transform()` method with a `Query` object containing the conversation history and follow-up query. The `transform()` method returns a new `Query` object with the compressed query text.  Consider setting a low temperature (e.g., 0.0) on the `ChatClient` for more deterministic results.','b39eb02e-9044-41c3-87fb-468f11c84975'),
('The `DocumentRetriever` interface is responsible for retrieving relevant `Document`s from an underlying data source based on a given `Query`. It acts as a functional interface, extending `Function<Query, List<Document>>` and providing a `retrieve` method for document retrieval.','This interface is a core component in Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems. Implementations like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` connect to specific data sources (e.g., vector stores, databases). It works with other components like `DocumentJoiner` and `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` to build complete RAG flows. It\'s often used in conjunction with `Query` and `Document` classes.','org.springframework.ai.rag.retrieval.search.DocumentRetriever','Implementations of `DocumentRetriever` are used to fetch documents based on a query. For example, `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` can be configured with a `vectorStore`, `similarityThreshold`, `topK` results, and optional `filterExpression` to retrieve semantically similar documents. Filter expressions can be static or dynamic, using a `Supplier` for context-aware filtering. Request-specific filters can also be provided through the `Query` object.','71be1fa1-dcaa-41a6-a304-48b426ac2dc6'),
('The `Operand` interface serves as a marker interface for different expression types used in filtering and searching within a vector database. It doesn\'t contain any methods but categorizes elements like keys, values, expressions, and groups.','This interface is foundational for building filter expressions used with `SearchRequest` and various vector store implementations (Weaviate, MongoDBAtlasVectorStore, PgVector, OracleVectorStore, Milvus). It\'s used in conjunction with `Filter.Expression` and `FilterExpressionBuilder` to create complex metadata filters for similarity searches.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.Operand','The `Operand` interface itself isn\'t directly instantiated. Instead, it\'s implemented by other classes that represent different parts of a filter expression. The primary usage involves constructing filter expressions using `FilterExpressionBuilder` and then passing them to the `similaritySearch` method of a `VectorStore` via a `SearchRequest`.  For example:\n\n```java\nFilterExpressionBuilder b = new FilterExpressionBuilder();\nvectorStore.similaritySearch(SearchRequest.builder()\n    .query(\"The World\")\n    .topK(TOP_K)\n    .filterExpression(b.and(\n        b.in(\"country\", \"UK\", \"NL\"),\n        b.gte(\"year\", 2020)).build()).build());\n```','c7130cd7-d240-4f52-8d06-4d2412bc88de'),
('This class is a Lexer generated by ANTLR4, responsible for lexical analysis of a filter expression language. It defines tokens and rules for parsing filter expressions used to query metadata associated with documents in a vector database.','This class is a core component of a filtering mechanism used in conjunction with a vector database and an embedding model. It works with `Filter.Expression` to parse and apply metadata filters to similarity searches. It\'s part of a system where an `EmbeddingModel` creates embeddings, a vector database stores them, and this Lexer enables filtering based on document metadata.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.FiltersLexer','The primary use case is parsing filter expressions (e.g., `country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020 && isActive == true`) to refine similarity searches in a vector database. The `FiltersLexer` tokenizes the input string, preparing it for parsing and evaluation. It\'s used internally by the `Filter.Expression` class to interpret the filter string.','47d199e2-fe65-4fc0-bf1b-4f3314487d90'),
('Represents a grouped boolean expression within a filter expression, likely used for parsing and evaluating complex filter conditions.','This class is part of a parser generated by ANTLR4, specifically related to `FiltersParser`, `BooleanExpressionContext`, `FiltersListener`, and `FiltersVisitor`. It\'s used to represent parenthesized expressions within a larger filter expression, which is used to filter documents based on their metadata in a vector database.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.GroupExpressionContext','This class is primarily used internally by the parser and visitor patterns generated by ANTLR4. It\'s not directly instantiated or used in client code, but rather represents a node in the parse tree of a filter expression.  A filter expression string like `(country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020)` would be parsed into a tree containing a `GroupExpressionContext` representing the parentheses and its contents.','401e3f84-478f-4f24-8299-548ba7c99031'),
('This class contains unit tests for the `FilterHelper` class, focusing on negating filter expressions and expanding `IN` and `NIN` expressions. It verifies that the `negate` method correctly transforms filter expressions to their logical opposites, and that `expandIn` and `expandNin` methods correctly convert `IN` and `NIN` expressions into equivalent expressions using `EQ` and `NE` operators.','This class tests the `FilterHelper` class, which likely provides utility methods for manipulating `Filter.Expression` objects. It also interacts with `FilterExpressionTextParser` to parse filter expressions from strings and `Filter.Expression` and related classes to represent and manipulate filter conditions. It is used in conjunction with `SearchRequest` and related classes for building and executing search queries with filters.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterHelperTests','The primary use case is to ensure the correctness of filter negation and expansion logic.  For example, `FilterHelper.negate(new FilterExpressionTextParser().parse(\"NOT key == \'UK\' \"))` should return an expression equivalent to `key != \'UK\'`.  The tests also demonstrate how `IN` and `NIN` expressions are expanded into a series of `EQ` or `NE` expressions, respectively.','73668cf1-83bf-48e8-9124-55526971f592'),
('This class is a builder for the `TranslationQueryTransformer`. It allows configuring the transformer with a `ChatClient.Builder`, a `PromptTemplate`, and a target language.','The `TranslationQueryTransformer` is a component used for pre-retrieval query transformation, specifically for translating queries to a target language. It relies on a `ChatClient` for language model interactions and a `PromptTemplate` for customizing the translation prompt. It\'s part of a larger system for retrieval-augmented generation (RAG).','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.transformation.Builder','To use this builder, first obtain an instance (typically through a factory method or similar). Then, chain calls to `chatClientBuilder()`, `promptTemplate()`, and `targetLanguage()` to configure the transformer. Finally, call `build()` to create the `TranslationQueryTransformer` instance.  For example:\n\n```java\nTranslationQueryTransformer transformer = TranslationQueryTransformer.builder()\n    .chatClientBuilder(chatClientBuilder)\n    .promptTemplate(promptTemplate)\n    .targetLanguage(\"es\")\n    .build();\n```','088e28b3-7570-4836-9c4b-59ff2a248875'),
('This class defines a set of constants representing the different types of vector stores supported by Spring AI. It serves as a central repository for these type identifiers, preventing hardcoding and ensuring consistency across the project.','This class is a utility class used throughout the Spring AI project to identify and configure different vector store implementations. It\'s referenced when specifying the vector store type in configuration files (e.g., application.yml) or programmatically when creating a VectorStore bean. It relates to classes like MongoDBAtlasVectorStore, MariaDBVectorStore, OpenSearchVectorStore, and others, as it provides the string identifiers used to instantiate them.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.SpringAIVectorStoreTypes','Use the constants defined in this class when configuring a vector store in your Spring AI application. For example, in `application.yml`, set `spring.ai.vectorstore.type` to one of the supported values (e.g., `azure`, `mongodb-atlas`, `pinecone`).  When creating a `VectorStore` bean programmatically, use these constants to specify the desired implementation.','140abae2-7ffc-4b3a-8ce4-5fd80a0917d5'),
('The RewriteQueryTransformer class uses a large language model to rewrite user queries, aiming to improve the quality of results when querying a target system like a vector store. It removes irrelevant information and ensures the query is concise and specific.','This class is a component within a Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline, specifically functioning as a \'Pre-Retrieval\' module to enhance query effectiveness. It interacts with a ChatClient for LLM interactions and can be integrated with other components like VectorStoreDocumentRetriever and RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor to build a complete RAG system.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.transformation.RewriteQueryTransformer','To use the RewriteQueryTransformer, first build an instance using its Builder, providing a ChatClient builder. Then, call the `transform` method with a Query object to obtain a rewritten query.  For example:\n\n```java\nQuery query = new Query(\"I\'m studying machine learning. What is an LLM?\");\n\nQueryTransformer queryTransformer = RewriteQueryTransformer.builder()\n        .chatClientBuilder(chatClientBuilder)\n        .build();\n\nQuery transformedQuery = queryTransformer.transform(query);\n```\n\nIt\'s recommended to configure the ChatClient with a low temperature (e.g., 0.0) for more deterministic results.','8c72f1f5-82b9-4d76-ae77-5ff19fc82b35'),
('The `VectorStoreObservationConvention` interface defines a convention for observations related to `VectorStoreObservationContext`. It extends the generic `ObservationConvention` interface and provides a default implementation for checking if a given `Observation.Context` is a `VectorStoreObservationContext`.','This interface is part of the Spring AI observability framework and is used to define how observations are handled for vector stores. It relates to classes like `ObservationConvention`, `VectorStoreObservationContext`, and `Observation`. It integrates with Micrometer for metrics and tracing, and is used by components like `VectorStore` to provide insights into their operations.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.VectorStoreObservationConvention','Implement this interface (or extend it) to customize observation behavior for specific vector store implementations. The default implementation checks if the context is a `VectorStoreObservationContext`, which is sufficient for basic usage.  The documentation shows how to use `VectorStore` with auto-configuration, including adding and searching documents, and deleting them. Observability is enabled through Spring Boot Actuator and provides metrics and tracing for `VectorStore` operations.','251036e5-68ca-4841-8495-7115b584821c'),
('This enum, `LowCardinalityKeyNames`, defines a set of key names used for adding metadata to observations related to vector store operations. These keys are designed to have a limited number of distinct values (low cardinality) and are used for metrics and tracing in Spring AI\'s observability features.','This enum is used within the Spring AI framework, particularly in components like `VectorStore` and related observability features. It integrates with Micrometer for metrics and tracing, providing insights into vector store operations. It\'s part of the broader Spring AI observability strategy, working alongside other observation attributes and the Spring Boot Actuator.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.LowCardinalityKeyNames','Use this enum to define consistent key names when adding metadata to observations related to vector store operations. For example, you can use `LowCardinalityKeyNames.DB_SYSTEM` to record the database system being used. These keys are intended for metrics and tracing, helping to monitor and analyze the performance and behavior of vector store interactions.','518818f6-aa74-46ba-a526-71a84d788143'),
('This class, `BooleanConstantContext`, represents a context node in a parse tree for boolean constant values within a filter expression. It extends `ConstantContext` and is generated by ANTLR4.','This class is part of the ANTLR4-generated parser for filter expressions used with the `Filter.Expression` class. It\'s a component of the DSL that allows users to define metadata filters for similarity searches in a vector database. It interacts with `FiltersListener` and `FiltersVisitor` interfaces for traversal and processing of the parse tree.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.BooleanConstantContext','This class is not directly used by application developers. It\'s an internal component of the filter expression parsing mechanism. It\'s used to represent and access the boolean value within a filter expression string (e.g., `isActive == true`).','ff3e5a7f-9e5c-4156-b507-72f8c555b668'),
('The `MultiQueryExpander` class expands a single query into multiple semantically diverse variations using a large language model. It\'s designed to improve retrieval by capturing different perspectives and addressing poorly formed or complex queries.','This class relies on a `ChatClient.Builder` to interact with a language model and a `PromptTemplate` to customize the expansion process. It\'s part of a larger system for query expansion and retrieval-augmented generation, potentially used in conjunction with components like `QueryTransformer` and `VectorStore`.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.expansion.Builder','To use the `MultiQueryExpander`, first obtain a `ChatClient.Builder`. Then, use the `MultiQueryExpander.builder()` to set the `chatClientBuilder`, the desired `numberOfQueries`, and optionally disable including the original query using `includeOriginal(false)`. Finally, call `build()` to create an instance and use the `expand()` method to generate a list of queries from a given input query.  The `promptTemplate()` method allows customization of the prompt used for query expansion.','a71736e4-398c-4421-8472-7719e37d6f17'),
('The `Key` record represents an expression key, typically used for filtering or identifying specific criteria within a dataset, such as a country code in a vector database search. It implements the `Operand` interface.','This class is used within the `Filter.Expression` system for defining metadata filters in `SearchRequest` objects. It\'s a fundamental building block for constructing complex filter conditions when querying a vector database. It relates to `Filter.Expression`, `SearchRequest`, and `Document` classes.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.Key','Create a `Key` instance to represent a specific filter criterion. For example, `Key key = new Key(\"NL\");` can be used within a `Filter.Expression` to filter documents where the \'country\' metadata is equal to \'NL\'.','c204bf96-de13-4b94-99b6-7776392eeedb'),
('Represents a \'NOT\' expression within a boolean expression context, used for filtering documents based on their metadata. It\'s part of a DSL for constructing filter expressions.','This class is a component of a larger filter expression system, likely used with a vector database to refine similarity searches. It interacts with `BooleanExpressionContext` and is processed by `FiltersListener` and `FiltersVisitor` during parsing and evaluation. It\'s used in conjunction with `Filter.Expression` to apply metadata filters to document retrieval.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.NotExpressionContext','This class is not directly instantiated but is generated by a parser (ANTLR4) when processing filter expressions.  For example, a filter expression like `! (country == \'UK\')` would result in the creation of a `NotExpressionContext` instance. The primary use is within the DSL for defining complex filter conditions.','95da7cf5-dcfa-4eb4-a8c6-7d64e067b72c'),
('The `QueryExpander` interface is a functional component designed to expand a single input query into a list of related queries. This is useful for handling poorly formed queries, generating alternative formulations, or breaking down complex queries into simpler ones.','This interface is implemented by classes like `MultiQueryExpander` which leverages a large language model for query expansion. It also works with components like `QueryTransformer` to process queries before or after expansion. It accepts a `Query` object as input and returns a `List<Query>`.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.expansion.QueryExpander','To expand a query, instantiate a `QueryExpander` implementation (e.g., `MultiQueryExpander`) and call its `expand` method. For example:\n\n```java\nMultiQueryExpander queryExpander = MultiQueryExpander.builder()\n    .chatClientBuilder(chatClientBuilder)\n    .numberOfQueries(3)\n    .build();\nList<Query> queries = queryExpander.expand(new Query(\"How to run a Spring Boot app?\"));\n```\n\nYou can customize the expansion process using builder methods like `numberOfQueries` and `includeOriginal`, and also customize the prompt used by the underlying language model via `promptTemplate()`.','72ec582d-a218-4168-8e65-7dd4704c678c'),
('This class, `IdentifierContext`, is a parser rule context generated by ANTLR4, representing the `identifier` rule in the `FiltersParser`. It provides access to the tokens that make up an identifier, such as identifiers themselves, dots, and quoted strings.','This class is part of the parser generated by ANTLR4 for defining a filter expression DSL. It\'s used in conjunction with `FiltersParser`, `FiltersListener`, and `FiltersVisitor` to parse and process filter expressions. It relates to the `Filter.Expression` mentioned in the documentation as it\'s a component of the DSL that accepts filter expressions as strings.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.IdentifierContext','This class is not directly used by application developers. It\'s an internal component of the parser. The documentation shows how filter expressions are used as strings (e.g., `country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020 && isActive == true`), and this class is involved in parsing those strings into a structured representation.','cb4c04d0-8c56-437c-93a4-8119db6408e7'),
('This class, `DescriptiveErrorListener`, is a custom error listener for ANTLR parsers. It captures syntax errors (line, character position, and message) during parsing and stores them in a thread-safe list (`errorMessages`). It extends `BaseErrorListener` to provide a specific implementation for handling syntax errors.','This class is designed to be used with ANTLR-based parsers. It interacts with the `Recognizer` to receive error notifications. It\'s a component that can be integrated into a parsing pipeline to provide detailed error reporting. It is related to classes like `Recognizer`, `RecognitionException`, and `BaseErrorListener`.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.DescriptiveErrorListener','Instantiate `DescriptiveErrorListener` (using the `INSTANCE` singleton) and add it as an error listener to an ANTLR parser. After parsing, access the `errorMessages` list to retrieve details about any syntax errors encountered. This is useful for providing informative error messages to users or for debugging parsing issues. Example: `parser.removeErrorListeners(); parser.addErrorListener(DescriptiveErrorListener.INSTANCE);`','383a26ee-b3b2-437b-888e-81d645e94b97'),
('This class implements the `DocumentJoiner` interface to combine lists of documents from multiple queries and data sources into a single, deduplicated list, sorted by score in descending order. It concatenates the documents, keeping the first occurrence in case of duplicates, and preserves the original scores.','This class is a concrete implementation of the `DocumentJoiner` interface. It works with `Document` objects, which are likely used by other components like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` and `RagService` for retrieval and processing in RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) applications. It\'s part of a pipeline that includes document retrieval, joining, and potentially generation of responses.','org.springframework.ai.rag.retrieval.join.ConcatenationDocumentJoiner','To use this class, provide a map where keys are `Query` objects and values are lists of lists of `Document` objects. The `join` method will return a single list of unique documents sorted by score. Example:\n\n```java\nMap<Query, List<List<Document>>> documentsForQuery = ...;\nDocumentJoiner documentJoiner = new ConcatenationDocumentJoiner();\nList<Document> documents = documentJoiner.join(documentsForQuery);\n```','e9382a70-e4af-4c5c-aa56-856a7e631ea2'),
('This class, `VectorStoreQueryResponseObservationHandler`, is an observation handler that intercepts and logs the query response from a VectorStore. It checks if the observation context is supported (specifically `VectorStoreObservationContext`) and, if so, logs the query response (a list of Documents) at the INFO level.','This class is part of the Spring AI observability features, specifically designed to work with `VectorStore` components. It utilizes `VectorStoreObservationContext` to determine if it should handle the observation and logs the response using SLF4J. It integrates with Micrometer for metrics and tracing, and is used within the broader Spring AI ecosystem for monitoring AI operations.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.VectorStoreQueryResponseObservationHandlerTests','To use this handler, it\'s automatically configured as part of Spring AI\'s observability setup when a `VectorStore` is used. No explicit instantiation is typically required. The key functionality is the logging of the query response, which can be enabled or disabled through configuration properties (e.g., `spring.ai.vectorstore.observations.log-query-response`). The example demonstrates how the handler logs the response when a `VectorStore`\'s `similaritySearch` method is called.','06c11634-16ea-4cbf-a4b5-86696fd92581'),
('The `Value` record represents a constant value (Numeric, Boolean, or String) or a constant array used as an operand in expressions. It\'s a simple data carrier for constant values.','This class implements the `Operand` interface, suggesting it\'s part of a larger expression evaluation or processing system. It\'s used in conjunction with classes like `Filter.Expression` and `SearchRequest` to define filter criteria and query parameters for vector database searches.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.Value','The primary use case is to encapsulate constant values within expressions. For example, when constructing a `Filter.Expression`, you would use `Value` to represent literal values in comparison operations (e.g., `country == \'UK\'`). It\'s a fundamental building block for defining search filters and query parameters.','5a9b6fe8-df4e-4c06-9225-8672037289a3'),
('This class represents an immutable content object storing text, metadata, and a vector embedding. It\'s designed for use in vector databases and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems. The class ensures thread safety and deep immutability of its fields.','This class serves as a data transfer object (DTO) representing content to be stored and retrieved from a vector store (e.g., MongoDBAtlasVectorStore, MariaDBVectorStore, OpenSearchVectorStore). It\'s used in conjunction with interfaces like `Content` and `VectorStore` to manage and query document embeddings. It also interacts with `Document` to prepare data for retrieval.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.SimpleVectorStoreContent','1. **Basic Content Creation:** Create an instance with text and an embedding vector: `SimpleVectorStoreContent content = new SimpleVectorStoreContent(\"My text\", embeddingVector);`\n2. **Content with Metadata:** Create an instance with text, metadata, and an embedding vector: `SimpleVectorStoreContent content = new SimpleVectorStoreContent(\"My text\", metadataMap, embeddingVector);`\n3. **Conversion to Document:** Convert the content to a `Document` object for use in retrieval: `Document document = content.toDocument(score);`','fcb8f877-2185-4d5f-8b73-8699b02200a0'),
('This class, `PineconeFilterExpressionConverter`, converts expressions into a filter format compatible with Pinecone\'s metadata filtering system. It extends `AbstractFilterExpressionConverter` and overrides methods to handle the specific syntax required by Pinecone.','This class is a specialized component likely used within a larger system for interacting with Pinecone vector databases. It relies on the `AbstractFilterExpressionConverter` for base functionality and interacts with `Expression` and `Key` objects to build the filter string. It\'s part of a broader effort to enable metadata filtering when querying Pinecone.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.converter.PineconeFilterExpressionConverter','The primary use case is to transform a structured expression (representing filter criteria) into a string that Pinecone can understand.  For example, to create a filter for documents where \'category\' is \'fiction\' AND \'author\' is \'Smith\', you would construct an `Expression` tree and then use this converter to generate the corresponding Pinecone filter string. The generated string would look like {\"$and\":[\"{category}:{fiction}\",\"{author}:{Smith}\"]}','aee117cc-dcee-42a6-90d5-8947e219f9cc'),
('This class contains integration tests for a `FilterExpressionTextParser`. The parser converts string-based filter expressions (similar to SQL WHERE clauses) into a structured `Expression` object. The tests cover various operators (EQ, GTE, IN, NE, AND, OR, NOT, NIN) and their combinations, including nested expressions and grouping. It also verifies that the parser caches the parsed expressions for reuse.','The `FilterExpressionTextParser` is used by components that need to parse and evaluate filter expressions, such as `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` and `SearchRequest`. It interacts with `Expression`, `Key`, and `Value` classes to represent the parsed filter logic. The `SearchRequest` class utilizes the parsed `Filter.Expression` to filter data in vector stores.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterExpressionTextParserTests','The primary use case is parsing filter expressions from strings into a structured format for efficient evaluation. Example: `Expression exp = parser.parse(\"genre == \'drama\' && year >= 2020\");`. The parser supports a range of operators and allows for complex boolean logic. The parsed expressions are cached for performance. The `SearchRequest.Builder` class provides a convenient way to build filter expressions programmatically or from strings using `filterExpression(String textExpression)`.','ae306bbf-de24-45cb-bb53-8e5c8d53c145'),
('The `FilterExpressionBuilder` class is a fluent builder for constructing filter expressions used to query vector stores. These expressions allow for metadata filtering of documents based on various criteria and operators.','This class is closely related to the `Filter.Expression` class, which represents the final filter expression. It\'s also used in conjunction with `SearchRequest` and vector store implementations (like `MongoDBAtlasVectorStore`, `OracleVectorStore`, `Milvus`, `Weaviate`) to filter search results. It is used by components like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` to refine queries.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterExpressionBuilderTests','The primary use case is building complex filter expressions programmatically.  For example:\n\n```java\nFilterExpressionBuilder b = new FilterExpressionBuilder();\nExpression expression = b.and(b.eq(\"genre\", \"drama\"), b.gte(\"year\", 2020)).build();\n```\n\nIt supports operators like `eq`, `gt`, `gte`, `lt`, `lte`, `ne`, `in`, `nin`, `not`, `and`, `or`, and `group` to create sophisticated filtering logic.  It can also be used with a string representation of the filter expression via `FilterExpressionTextParser`.','754843cd-0b73-4d1d-9cb5-92bef05c2b27'),
('This class, `CommonVectorStoreProperties`, encapsulates a common property used by various vector store implementations: whether to initialize the schema on application startup. It provides a boolean flag `initializeSchema` to control this behavior.','This class serves as a base or shared configuration class for different vector store implementations (e.g., `MongoDBAtlasVectorStore`, `OpenSearchVectorStore`). It\'s likely used as a parent class or a property source for these specific vector store configurations. It is part of the `spring-ai` project and interacts with Spring Boot\'s configuration mechanism via `application.yml` or `application.properties`.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.properties.CommonVectorStoreProperties','The primary use case is to enable or disable schema initialization for vector stores.  Set `initialize-schema: true` in your Spring Boot configuration (e.g., `application.yml`) to automatically initialize the schema when the application starts. This is useful for ensuring the vector store is ready to accept data immediately. Example:\n\nspring:\n  ai:\n    vectorstore:\n      mongodb:\n        initialize-schema: true','512b7444-b73b-4db8-811c-940ce44bc50c'),
('This class, `VectorStoreRuntimeHintsTests`, is designed to test the registration of runtime hints specifically for vector stores. These hints are crucial for ahead-of-time (AOT) compilation, ensuring that necessary resources are included during the build process, particularly ANTLR grammar files used for filtering.','This class is a test suite for the `VectorStoreRuntimeHints` class. It verifies that the hints are correctly registered with the `RuntimeHints` object, which is a core component of Spring\'s AOT support. It ensures the necessary ANTLR grammar file (`Filters.g4`) is included for vector store filtering functionality.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.aot.VectorStoreRuntimeHintsTests','The primary use case is to ensure that the vector store components are correctly configured for AOT compilation. The tests verify that the `VectorStoreRuntimeHints` class correctly registers the required resources (specifically the ANTLR grammar file) with the `RuntimeHints` object. This is done by asserting that the `RuntimeHints` object contains the expected resource hint. The tests also confirm that providing a null ClassLoader does not cause exceptions.','1c2d852d-8455-4932-8d3c-948ae3f9c86e'),
('The `FilterExpressionTextParser` class parses a textual filter expression language (similar to SQL WHERE clauses) into a `Filter.Expression` object. It uses an ANTLR4 grammar to define the language and provides caching for performance. It handles various operators like AND, OR, IN, NIN, equals, greater than, less than, and more.','This class is used by components like `SearchRequest` (via its Builder) to parse filter expressions provided as strings. It interacts with the `Filter` interface and its related types (`Filter.Expression`, `Filter.Operand`, etc.) to represent the parsed filter. It\'s a core component for enabling metadata filtering in vector search operations.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterExpressionTextParser','1. **Parsing a filter expression:** `FilterExpressionTextParser parser = new FilterExpressionTextParser(); Filter.Expression expression = parser.parse(\"country == \'BG\' && year >= 2020\");`\n2. **Using in a SearchRequest:** `SearchRequest request = SearchRequest.builder().query(\"some query\").filterExpression(\"country == \'US\'\").build();`\n3. **Clearing the cache:** `parser.clearCache();` (useful for testing or when filter expressions are dynamically updated).','ce08bbfc-6e62-4b34-939a-96320d567384'),
('The `Filter` class provides a portable way to generate metadata filter expressions for vector stores. It allows building complex filters using operations like equality, inequality, greater than, less than, IN, and NOT, combined with AND and OR logic. These expressions can then be converted into vector-store specific native expressions.','This class is used by components like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` and `SearchRequest` to filter documents based on metadata. It interacts with various vector store implementations (MongoDBAtlasVectorStore, OracleVectorStore, Milvus, Weaviate) through the `filterExpression` parameter in `similaritySearch` methods. It also works with `FilterExpressionBuilder` for programmatic filter creation and `FilterExpressionTextParser` for parsing filter expressions from strings.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.Filter','The primary use case is to define filters for retrieving documents from vector stores.  You can create filters programmatically using `FilterExpressionBuilder`:\n\n```java\nFilterExpressionBuilder b = new FilterExpressionBuilder();\nExpression expression = b.eq(\"country\", \"BG\").build();\n```\n\nOr, you can use a string-based expression:\n\n```java\nvectorStore.similaritySearch(\n    SearchRequest.builder()\n    .query(\"The World\")\n    .filterExpression(\"author in [\'john\', \'jill\'] && article_type == \'blog\'\").build());\n```\n\nCommon operators include `EQ`, `NE`, `GT`, `GTE`, `LT`, `LTE`, `IN`, `NIN`, `AND`, and `OR`.','15466364-eac1-47e0-9486-9a25cd1cd6c1'),
('The `EmbeddingMath` class provides static utility methods for performing mathematical operations on float arrays, specifically related to embeddings. It includes methods for calculating cosine similarity, dot product, and vector norm.','This class is a utility class and does not directly relate to other classes in the provided documentation. It likely serves as a helper for vector store implementations (MongoDBAtlasVectorStore, MariaDBVectorStore, OpenSearchVectorStore, etc.) and embedding models used within the Spring AI framework to calculate similarity between vectors.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.EmbeddingMath','The primary use case is calculating the similarity between two vectors. For example:\n\n```java\nfloat[] vector1 = {0.1f, 0.2f, 0.3f};\nfloat[] vector2 = {0.4f, 0.5f, 0.6f};\ndouble similarity = EmbeddingMath.cosineSimilarity(vector1, vector2);\n```\n\nIt\'s also used internally by vector stores to determine the similarity of embeddings during search operations.','d811928d-9507-43c8-a8a7-9fe1402bd67c'),
('Represents an integer constant within a filter expression. This class is part of the parser generated by ANTLR4 and provides access to the tokens representing the integer value, plus or minus signs.','This class extends `ConstantContext` and is used by the `FiltersParser` and related listener/visitor interfaces (`FiltersListener`, `FiltersVisitor`). It\'s a component of the filter expression DSL used for querying vector databases, specifically for metadata filtering of `Document` objects.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.IntegerConstantContext','This class is primarily used internally by the parser and its associated listener/visitor implementations. It\'s not directly instantiated or used in client code. Instead, it\'s a result of parsing a filter expression string (e.g., `year > 2020`) and provides access to the parsed integer values.','e0cc98c3-753b-4604-adc6-a32fd017399b'),
('This interface defines a visitor for the parse tree generated by the `FiltersParser`, which is used to process filter expressions. It provides methods to visit different nodes of the parse tree, representing various filter components like boolean expressions, comparisons, constants, and identifiers.','This interface is central to processing filter expressions used with the `similaritySearch` methods of a vector database. It works in conjunction with the `Filter.Expression` class and an ANTLR4-based DSL to enable SQL-like filtering of document metadata. The `EmbeddingModel` is used to create embeddings, which are then used in the vector database along with these filters.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.FiltersVisitor','Implementations of this interface are used to traverse the parse tree generated from filter expressions (e.g., `country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020 && isActive == true`) and evaluate them. The visitor pattern allows for custom logic to be applied to each node in the tree, enabling flexible filter processing. The `FiltersParser` generates the parse tree that this visitor operates on.','eecc997c-32d6-4fd4-8fb2-a3766920f904'),
('This class, `ConstantContext`, is a parser rule context representing a constant within a grammar defined using ANTLR4. It extends `ParserRuleContext` and serves as a base for representing constant elements during parsing.','This class is part of an ANTLR4 grammar implementation, likely used for parsing expressions or data formats that include constants. It\'s a foundational element in the parsing process, working with other context classes to build a parse tree.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.ConstantContext','The `ConstantContext` class is primarily used internally by the ANTLR4 parser. Developers typically don\'t interact with it directly but rather rely on the generated parser code to create and manage instances of this class during the parsing process. It\'s a building block for representing the structure of the input being parsed.','94539dd5-16bd-4254-b2ae-a4a485e81dd6'),
('This class, `FilterExpressionVisitor`, is a visitor pattern implementation that parses filter expressions (defined using ANTLR4) and converts them into a `Filter.Operand` hierarchy. It handles various expression types like comparisons, logical operations (AND, OR, NOT), IN/NIN, and constant values (text, integer, decimal, boolean, long, and arrays).','This class is a core component for processing filter expressions used in vector store searches, particularly in conjunction with classes like `SearchRequest`, `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever`, and the `Filter.Expression` class itself. It interacts with the ANTLR4 generated parser (`FiltersParser`) to traverse the expression tree. It\'s used by components responsible for querying vector databases and applying metadata filters.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterExpressionVisitor','The primary use case is to translate a filter expression string (e.g., `country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020`) into a structured `Filter.Expression` object that can be used to filter search results.  For example:\n\n1.  Parsing a filter expression string: `new FilterExpressionTextParser().parse(\"author in [\'john\', \'jill\'] && article_type == \'blog\'\")`\n2.  Building expressions programmatically using `FilterExpressionBuilder`: `b.and(b.in(\"author\",\"john\", \"jill\"), b.eq(\"article_type\", \"blog\")).build()`\n3.  Using the resulting `Filter.Expression` within a `SearchRequest` to filter vector store searches.','44a6506e-5335-4e46-a9aa-a6d702ecad21'),
('This class is a builder for creating `CompressionQueryTransformer` instances. The `CompressionQueryTransformer` uses a large language model to compress a conversation history and a follow-up query into a standalone query.','This class relates to `ChatClient.Builder`, `PromptTemplate`, and `CompressionQueryTransformer`. It\'s used to configure and build a `CompressionQueryTransformer` which is a type of `QueryTransformer` used in pre-retrieval processing. It relies on a `ChatClient` for LLM interactions and a `PromptTemplate` for customizing the compression prompt.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.transformation.Builder','To use this builder, first obtain a `ChatClient.Builder` instance. Then, use the `chatClientBuilder()` and `promptTemplate()` methods to configure the transformer. Finally, call `build()` to create the `CompressionQueryTransformer` instance.  Example:\n```java\nCompressionQueryTransformer queryTransformer = CompressionQueryTransformer.builder()\n        .chatClientBuilder(chatClientBuilder)\n        .build();\n```','eb5efd16-82a6-4250-b35a-a8c3eafcf22e'),
('The `PromptAssert` class provides static methods for validating prompt templates and ensuring they contain required placeholders. It helps prevent errors by verifying that essential placeholders are present before a prompt is used.','This class is a utility class focused on prompt validation and doesn\'t have direct relationships with other core classes like `EmbeddingModel` or `VectorStore`. It\'s likely used internally within components responsible for prompt creation and management, ensuring data integrity before prompts are sent to AI models.','org.springframework.ai.rag.util.PromptAssert','The primary use case is to assert that a `PromptTemplate` contains specific placeholders. For example:\n\n```java\nPromptTemplate myTemplate = // ... your template initialization ...;\nString[] requiredPlaceholders = {\"{name}\", \"{context}\"};\nPromptAssert.templateHasRequiredPlaceholders(myTemplate, requiredPlaceholders);\n```\n\nThis code snippet checks if `myTemplate` contains both \"{name}\" and \"{context}\" placeholders. If either is missing, an `IllegalArgumentException` is thrown, preventing potential runtime errors.','4e7b6b14-fd77-4a38-9fe8-aa6f7b7be7d0'),
('Abstract base class for VectorStore implementations that provides observation capabilities using Micrometer for metrics and tracing. It handles observation registration, embedding models, and batching strategies. Concrete implementations need to provide the actual add, delete, and similarity search logic.','This class serves as a foundation for concrete VectorStore implementations (e.g., CosmosDBVectorStore). It interacts with components like EmbeddingModel, ObservationRegistry, VectorStoreObservationConvention, and BatchingStrategy. It\'s part of the spring-ai-vector-store module and integrates with the Spring ecosystem for observability through Micrometer.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.AbstractObservationVectorStore','Extend this class to create a new VectorStore. Implement the `doAdd`, `doDelete`, and `doSimilaritySearch` methods to provide the specific vector store logic. Use the builder pattern to configure the store with an EmbeddingModel and ObservationRegistry. The example demonstrates adding documents, performing a similarity search, and deleting documents using a CosmosDBVectorStore.','d569bc1d-d7f3-40e1-a45a-ad407c843420'),
('The `SearchRequest` class represents a search request with parameters like query, top K results, similarity threshold, and a filter expression. It provides a builder pattern for constructing requests and a `from` method for creating copies with modifications.','This class is central to performing similarity searches against a vector store. It interacts with components like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` to retrieve relevant documents based on the specified criteria. It also utilizes `Filter.Expression` for metadata filtering and `FilterExpressionBuilder` for constructing filter expressions. It is used by retrieval modules to query data systems.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.SearchRequestTests','1. **Basic Search:** Create a `SearchRequest` with just a query string using the builder: `SearchRequest.builder().query(\"your query\").build()`. 2. **Filtering:** Add a filter expression to refine the search: `SearchRequest.builder().query(\"your query\").filterExpression(\"country == \'USA\'\").build()`.  Alternatively, use `FilterExpressionBuilder`: `SearchRequest.builder().query(\"your query\").filterExpression(new FilterExpressionBuilder().eq(\"country\", \"USA\").build()).build()`. 3. **Copying and Modifying:** Create a copy of an existing request and modify it: `SearchRequest newRequest = SearchRequest.from(originalRequest).topK(10).build()`.','646a1e82-5384-4808-9369-af5572b46e3e'),
('This class is a Builder for the `RewriteQueryTransformer`, responsible for rewriting user queries to improve search results in a target system. It allows configuring the `ChatClient`, `PromptTemplate`, and the target search system.','The `RewriteQueryTransformer` is a component within a larger retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) pipeline. It utilizes a `ChatClient` (configured via its builder) and a `PromptTemplate` to rewrite queries. It\'s part of a suite of `QueryTransformer` classes (like `CompressionQueryTransformer` and `TranslationQueryTransformer`) used for pre-retrieval query processing.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.transformation.Builder','To use the `RewriteQueryTransformer`, first obtain a `ChatClient.Builder`, then use the `RewriteQueryTransformer.Builder` to configure it with the `ChatClient.Builder`, an optional `PromptTemplate`, and the target search system. Finally, call `build()` to create an instance of the `RewriteQueryTransformer`. Example:\n\n```java\nQuery query = new Query(\"I\'m studying machine learning. What is an LLM?\");\n\nQueryTransformer queryTransformer = RewriteQueryTransformer.builder()\n        .chatClientBuilder(chatClientBuilder)\n        .build();\n\nQuery transformedQuery = queryTransformer.transform(query);\n```','fcd2b7a5-0460-4a19-aec3-b0cbb40dba6d'),
('The `Group` record represents an expression grouping, used to enforce precedence in evaluations. It encapsulates another `Expression` as its content.','This class implements the `Operand` interface and is used within a larger expression evaluation framework. It\'s a building block for constructing more complex expressions.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.Group','The primary use case is to wrap expressions to control the order of operations. For example, `new Group(new Add(new Number(1), new Number(2)))` groups the addition operation.','e00e1e00-13b2-4a80-a88b-b6492db4c578'),
('The `ContextualQueryAugmenter` class augments a user query with contextual data retrieved from documents. It uses prompt templates to format the augmented query and allows for customization of how empty contexts are handled. It\'s a core component in Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) pipelines.','This class is part of the `spring-ai-rag` module and is often used in conjunction with `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` and `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` to build RAG flows. It interacts with other Spring AI modules like `spring-ai-model` for prompt templating and `spring-ai-vector-store` for document retrieval. It\'s designed to be integrated into a `ChatClient` via `Advisor`s.','org.springframework.ai.rag.generation.augmentation.Builder','The primary use case is to enhance a user\'s query with relevant information from a vector store.  The builder pattern is used to configure the augmenter:\n\n```java\nQueryAugmenter queryAugmenter = ContextualQueryAugmenter.builder()\n        .allowEmptyContext(true)\n        .build();\n```\n\nIt can also be used with custom prompt templates:\n\n```java\nPromptTemplate promptTemplate = PromptTemplate.from(\"your custom prompt template\");\nQueryAugmenter queryAugmenter = ContextualQueryAugmenter.builder()\n        .promptTemplate(promptTemplate)\n        .build();\n```','764ca213-62dd-4762-b7df-b8d2a9df527a'),
('This class `SimpleVectorStoreFilterExpressionConverterTests` tests the conversion of filter expressions into a format suitable for vector stores. It uses the `SimpleVectorStoreFilterExpressionConverter` to convert `Filter.Expression` objects into string expressions that can be evaluated using Spring Expression Language (SpEL). The tests cover various filter operations like EQ, AND, GTE, IN, OR, and NIN, as well as different data types such as dates, strings, booleans, and decimals.','This class tests the `SimpleVectorStoreFilterExpressionConverter` which is likely a component responsible for translating filter criteria into a format understandable by a vector database or search engine. It interacts with `Filter.Expression`, `StandardEvaluationContext`, and `SpelExpressionParser` from the Spring Framework to perform the conversion and evaluation. It\'s part of a larger system dealing with filtering and querying data stored in a vector store.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.converter.SimpleVectorStoreFilterExpressionConverterTests','The primary use case is to verify that the `SimpleVectorStoreFilterExpressionConverter` correctly translates filter expressions into SpEL expressions.  A key example is converting a date filter (`activationDate`) into a string representation like \'#metadata[\\\'activationDate\\\'] == \\\'2024-01-07T14:29:12Z\\\'\', which can then be evaluated against metadata associated with vector store entries. Another important example is combining multiple filters using AND/OR operations to create complex queries.','e65e2dba-cea6-4f3d-9c0c-b92458f32f4e'),
('This interface defines a listener for parse trees generated by the `FiltersParser`, enabling traversal and processing of filter expressions.','This interface is closely related to `FiltersParser`, acting as a handler for the parse tree it produces. It\'s used to interpret filter expressions (similar to SQL \'where\' clauses) applied to document metadata during similarity searches in a vector database. The documentation mentions `Filter.Expression` which is processed using this parser.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.FiltersListener','Implement this interface to create a custom listener that processes filter expressions. The `enter` and `exit` methods for each grammar rule (e.g., `where`, `booleanExpression`, `constant`) are called as the parser traverses the parse tree. This allows you to build a representation or perform validation of the filter expression.','1948a987-0256-42ef-a6f5-bb60ee1655c5'),
('The DocumentPostProcessor interface defines a functional interface for post-processing a list of documents retrieved in response to a query. It allows for operations like re-ranking, filtering, and compression to improve the quality and relevance of the retrieved information before it\'s used by a language model.','This interface is used within a Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline, specifically by components like `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` to refine the documents obtained from a `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` before they are passed to a `ChatClient`. It works alongside `Query` and `Document` objects and embedding models.','org.springframework.ai.rag.postretrieval.document.DocumentPostProcessor','Implementations of `DocumentPostProcessor` can be used to customize the document processing step in a RAG pipeline. Common use cases include re-ranking documents based on relevance to the query, removing irrelevant or redundant documents, and compressing document content to fit within model context windows. The interface is a functional interface, allowing for concise implementations using lambda expressions.','0d44bd03-329d-412c-9928-bd8e2a14bbbb'),
('This class tests the functionality of the `SimpleVectorStore` for storing and retrieving documents based on their embeddings. It covers adding documents, similarity search, deletion, saving/loading the store, handling edge cases like empty lists, null values, and concurrent operations, and validating similarity thresholds.','This class interacts directly with `SimpleVectorStore` and `EmbeddingModel`. It uses Mockito to mock the `EmbeddingModel` for controlled testing. It also utilizes Spring\'s `@TempDir` annotation for creating temporary files during save/load tests. It\'s a unit test class designed to verify the correct behavior of the `SimpleVectorStore` component.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.SimpleVectorStoreTests','1. **Adding and Retrieving Documents:** Demonstrates adding a single document or multiple documents and then retrieving them using similarity search.\n2. **Saving and Loading:** Shows how to save the vector store to a file and load it back, ensuring data persistence.\n3. **Similarity Search with Threshold:** Illustrates using a similarity threshold to filter search results, returning only documents above a certain similarity score.\n4. **Handling Edge Cases:** Tests the store\'s behavior with empty or null document lists, and deletion of non-existent documents.','6084ddae-9a80-42c3-88e2-bee2f34e523b'),
('This class is a parser generated by ANTLR4, designed to parse filter expressions for metadata filtering in a vector database. It defines the grammar for a \'where\' clause-like syntax to filter documents based on their metadata key-value pairs.','This class is used in conjunction with the `EmbeddingModel` and `VectorDatabase` components. The `EmbeddingModel` generates embeddings, the `VectorDatabase` stores them, and `FiltersParser` is used to parse filter expressions that refine similarity searches within the `VectorDatabase` based on document metadata.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.FiltersParser','The primary use case is parsing filter expressions provided as strings. For example, a filter expression like `country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020 && isActive == true` would be parsed by this class to enable filtering of documents based on these criteria. The parsed expression is then used to filter results from the vector database\'s similarity search.','0572599f-a3f1-4328-beda-c1c4563bfa26'),
('The TranslationQueryTransformer class translates a user query to a target language supported by the embedding model, using a large language model. It returns the original query if it\'s already in the target language or if the source language is unknown.','This class is a component used in the pre-retrieval phase of a Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline. It implements the QueryTransformer interface and works with ChatClient to perform the translation. It\'s part of a larger ETL pipeline for processing data and preparing it for AI models.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.transformation.TranslationQueryTransformer','To use the TranslationQueryTransformer, first build an instance using the Builder, providing a ChatClient builder and the target language. Then, call the transform method with a Query object to get the translated query. Example:\nQuery query = new Query(\"Hvad er Danmarks hovedstad?\");\nQueryTransformer queryTransformer = TranslationQueryTransformer.builder()\n    .chatClientBuilder(chatClientBuilder)\n    .targetLanguage(\"english\")\n    .build();\nQuery transformedQuery = queryTransformer.transform(query);','94d4865d-073e-46eb-bb82-c1e0f7436a2a'),
('This class, `ConstantArrayContext`, represents the context of a constant array within a grammar defined by `FiltersParser`. It provides access to the tokens that make up the array, including the opening and closing square brackets, commas separating the constants, and the constant values themselves.','This class is part of a parser generated by ANTLR4, specifically for the `FiltersParser`. It\'s a rule context, meaning it represents a specific production rule (constant array) in the grammar. It interacts with other contexts like `ConstantContext` (representing individual constants) and is used by listeners and visitors (`FiltersListener`, `FiltersVisitor`) to process the parsed filter expressions.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.ConstantArrayContext','This class is primarily used internally by the parser to represent the structure of a constant array during parsing.  It\'s not directly instantiated or used by application code. Instead, it\'s used by the parser to provide a structured representation of the input filter expression, which can then be traversed by listeners or visitors to perform actions like validation or code generation. The `constant()` methods are used to access the individual constant values within the array.','14af454d-0abf-4491-af4d-c7763878c7bc'),
('This class, `InNinTestConverter`, extends `PrintFilterExpressionConverter` and overrides the `doExpression` method to handle `IN` and `NIN` expression types. It delegates to `FilterHelper` to expand these expressions within a filter context. For other expression types, it falls back to the superclass\'s implementation.','This class is a specialized converter within a filter expression processing pipeline. It works with `Expression` objects and interacts with `FilterHelper` to expand specific filter types (`IN` and `NIN`). It\'s part of a larger system for building and applying metadata filters to vector stores, as used by components like `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` and `SearchRequest`.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.InNinTestConverter','This converter is used internally by the filter expression processing logic to handle `IN` and `NIN` operators when converting filter expressions into a format suitable for the underlying vector store. It\'s not directly instantiated or used by application code, but rather is invoked as part of the expression evaluation process. Example: A `SearchRequest` might contain a filter expression like `author in [\'john\', \'jill\']`, which would be processed by this converter during the conversion to a vector store-specific filter.','c3f879e5-fe6c-4442-92eb-c7af92505886'),
('SimpleVectorStore is a basic implementation of a vector store that provides functionalities to add, delete, and search vectors based on similarity. It supports saving and loading vector data from files in JSON format. It extends AbstractObservationVectorStore and utilizes an embedding model to generate vector representations of documents.','This class is part of the spring-ai-vector-store module and interacts with components like EmbeddingModel for generating embeddings, Document for representing data, and SearchRequest for defining search parameters. It can be used with other Spring AI modules like spring-ai-client-chat and spring-ai-rag for building conversational AI applications and RAG pipelines. It also relates to various vector database implementations like MongoDB, OpenSearch, and Pinecone through the VectorStore interface.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.SimpleVectorStore','1. **Initialization:** Use the `SimpleVectorStore.builder(embeddingModel)` method to create a builder instance, providing an `EmbeddingModel`.  2. **Adding Documents:** Use the `doAdd` method to add a list of `Document` objects to the store. The embedding for each document is generated using the provided `EmbeddingModel`. 3. **Similarity Search:** Use the `doSimilaritySearch` method with a `SearchRequest` object to perform a similarity search. The request specifies the query, top-k results, and similarity threshold. 4. **Saving and Loading:** Use the `save` and `load` methods to persist the vector store\'s content to a file and load it from a file, respectively.','1c63079a-1158-4fd8-8a0d-cc3167638019'),
('Represents the \'where\' clause context in a filter expression, as defined by the Filters grammar. It parses and holds information about the WHERE keyword and the associated boolean expression.','This class is part of an ANTLR4-generated parser for filter expressions used with a vector database\'s similarity search functionality. It works in conjunction with `BooleanExpressionContext` and `FiltersListener`/`FiltersVisitor` to process and evaluate filter conditions applied to document metadata. It\'s used by the `Filter.Expression` class to provide a DSL for filtering search results.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.WhereContext','This class is not directly instantiated but is a result of parsing a filter expression string. It\'s used internally by the parser to represent the \'where\' clause.  For example, if a filter expression is `country == \'UK\' && year > 2020`, the parser will create a `WhereContext` instance to represent the `WHERE` part and a `BooleanExpressionContext` to represent the condition itself.','6ebc773a-20d0-4cd5-a481-d243421d186f'),
('This class, `PrintFilterExpressionConverter`, is responsible for converting an `Expression` object into a human-readable string representation suitable for display or debugging. It handles different expression components like operands, operators, and grouping.','This class extends `AbstractFilterExpressionConverter` and is likely part of a larger system for processing and representing filter expressions. It doesn\'t directly relate to the tool-related classes (like `MethodToolCallback`, `ToolDefinition`, etc.) described in the documentation, but it could be used within a tool to format its input or output.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.converter.PrintFilterExpressionConverter','The primary use case is to traverse an expression tree and build a string representation.  For example, to convert an expression, you would create an instance of this class and call its `doExpression` method with the expression and a `StringBuilder` to accumulate the result. The `doKey`, `doStartGroup`, and `doEndGroup` methods handle specific expression elements.','50568edb-49cf-4557-89b0-d282e3d12b80'),
('This class is a base visitor for a parse tree generated by a `FiltersParser`. It provides empty implementations for all visit methods defined in the `FiltersVisitor` interface, simply delegating to the default `visitChildren` method. This allows developers to easily create custom visitors that only need to handle a specific subset of filter expression types.','This class is part of a filter expression evaluation system, likely used to process metadata filters for similarity searches in a vector database. It works with the output of an ANTLR4-based parser (`FiltersParser`) and implements the `FiltersVisitor` interface. The documentation mentions `Filter.Expression` which this class helps to process.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.FiltersBaseVisitor','Extend this class to create a custom visitor to handle specific filter expression types. Override the relevant `visit...` methods to implement the desired logic for processing each expression. For example, to handle only \'Where\' expressions, override only the `visitWhere` method.','2f8667a0-832f-45bf-ab7f-d2e52f66c502'),
('The `MultiQueryExpander` class expands a given query into multiple semantically diverse variations using a large language model. This is useful for improving search recall by capturing different perspectives and increasing the chances of finding relevant information.','This class implements the `QueryExpander` interface and relies on a `ChatClient` to interact with the language model. It can be used in conjunction with other query transformation components like `TranslationQueryTransformer` to further refine search queries.','org.springframework.ai.rag.preretrieval.query.expansion.MultiQueryExpander','To use the `MultiQueryExpander`, first build an instance using the `builder()` method, providing a `ChatClient` builder and optionally customizing the number of queries to generate and whether to include the original query. Then, call the `expand()` method with the original `Query` to obtain a list of expanded queries.\n\nExample:\n```java\nMultiQueryExpander expander = MultiQueryExpander.builder()\n    .chatClientBuilder(chatClientBuilder)\n    .numberOfQueries(3)\n    .build();\nList<Query> queries = expander.expand(new Query(\"How to run a Spring Boot app?\"));\n```\n\nTo exclude the original query:\n```java\nMultiQueryExpander expander = MultiQueryExpander.builder()\n    .chatClientBuilder(chatClientBuilder)\n    .includeOriginal(false)\n    .build();\n```','f65d7866-7541-4aae-a476-d6c839537099'),
('The RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor class implements common Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) flows, orchestrating query transformation, expansion, document retrieval, joining, post-processing, and augmentation before interacting with a chat model. It enhances prompts with relevant context retrieved from a document store.','This class is a core component of the `spring-ai-rag` module, interacting with interfaces like `QueryTransformer`, `QueryExpander`, `DocumentRetriever`, `DocumentJoiner`, `DocumentPostProcessor`, and `QueryAugmenter`. It integrates with the `ChatClient` through the `Advisor` interface, and utilizes `TaskExecutor` and `Scheduler` for asynchronous operations. It\'s part of a broader ecosystem including `spring-ai-commons`, `spring-ai-model`, `spring-ai-vector-store`, and `spring-ai-client-chat`.','org.springframework.ai.rag.advisor.RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor','To use the `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor`, build an instance using the `Builder`, configuring components like `DocumentRetriever` (e.g., `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever`) and optionally `QueryExpander` and `DocumentPostProcessor`. Then, add the advisor to a `ChatClient`\'s prompt using the `advisors()` method before calling the chat model. Example:\n\n```java\nRetrievalAugmentationAdvisor retrievalAugmentationAdvisor = RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor.builder()\n        .documentRetriever(VectorStoreDocumentRetriever.builder()\n                .similarityThreshold(0.50)\n                .vectorStore(vectorStore)\n                .build())\n        .build();\n\nString answer = chatClient.prompt()\n        .advisors(retrievalAugmentationAdvisor)\n        .user(question)\n        .call()\n        .content();\n```','22af6666-4521-4144-b6f0-d9dd34d1b913'),
('The `VectorStoreObservationContext` class is a data transfer object (DTO) used to encapsulate information about operations performed on a vector store. It holds details like the database system, operation name (add, query, delete, etc.), collection name, dimensions, field name, namespace, and similarity metric. It\'s designed to be used with observability frameworks to track and monitor vector store interactions.','This class is a core component of the Spring AI project, specifically within the `spring-ai-vector-store` module. It\'s used by `VectorStore` implementations to provide context for observability, allowing for metrics and tracing of vector store operations. It integrates with Micrometer for metric collection and tracing. It\'s also used in the `DemoApplication` example to demonstrate vector store usage.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.VectorStoreObservationContextTests','To create an instance of `VectorStoreObservationContext`, use the builder pattern. Always provide a non-null and non-empty database system and operation name. Optional fields like collection name, dimensions, field name, namespace, and similarity metric can be set as needed. Example:\n\n```java\nVectorStoreObservationContext context = VectorStoreObservationContext.builder(\"my_db\", VectorStoreObservationContext.Operation.QUERY)\n    .collectionName(\"my_collection\")\n    .similarityMetric(\"cosine\")\n    .build();\n```','7a0cd27c-6102-4c65-8a84-da038432b439'),
('The `FilterExpressionConverter` interface is responsible for converting a generic `Filter.Expression` into a string representation suitable for a specific vector store\'s query language. This allows for portable filter expressions to be translated into a format understood by the underlying database.','This interface is used in conjunction with `Filter.Expression` to provide a flexible way to filter data in vector stores. It\'s a key component in the `SearchRequest` and `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` classes, enabling metadata filtering during similarity searches. It interacts with various vector store implementations (MongoDBAtlasVectorStore, PgVector, OracleVectorStore, Milvus) to translate the filter expression into their specific query formats.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.FilterExpressionConverter','Implementations of this interface are used to adapt filter expressions to different vector store technologies. The primary use case is within a `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever` to apply metadata filters during a similarity search.  You can either provide a filter expression as a string directly in the `SearchRequest` or programmatically using `Filter.Expression` and a `FilterExpressionBuilder`. For example:\n\n```java\nFilterExpressionBuilder b = new FilterExpressionBuilder();\nvectorStore.similaritySearch(SearchRequest.builder()\n    .query(\"The World\")\n    .topK(TOP_K)\n    .similarityThreshold(SIMILARITY_THRESHOLD)\n    .filterExpression(b.and(\n        b.in(\"author\",\"john\", \"jill\"),\n        b.eq(\"article_type\", \"blog\")).build()).build());\n```','c3b00783-4cf8-4345-a7d4-dadc0bd8765b'),
('The `Builder` class is used to construct a `VectorStoreObservationContext` object, which encapsulates configuration details for vector store operations. It provides a fluent interface for setting properties like database system, operation name, collection name, dimensions, field name, namespace, query request, query response, and similarity metric.','This class is a helper class for creating `VectorStoreObservationContext` objects, which are likely used within a larger vector store implementation (like `CosmosDBVectorStore`) to provide observability and context for interactions with the vector store. It\'s part of the `spring-ai-vector-store` module and interacts with components like `SearchRequest` and `Document` from `spring-ai-commons`.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.Builder','The primary use case is to create a `VectorStoreObservationContext` with specific configuration details.  For example:\n\n```java\nVectorStoreObservationContext context = new VectorStoreObservationContext.Builder(\"CosmosDB\", \"similaritySearch\")\n    .collectionName(\"myCollection\")\n    .dimensions(1536)\n    .queryRequest(SearchRequest.builder().query(\"example query\").build())\n    .build();\n```\n\nThis allows for structured logging and monitoring of vector store interactions.','c5ede087-a28b-44a4-aabe-db10c32514af'),
('This class, `VectorStoreQueryResponseObservationHandler`, is an observation handler that logs the query response content from a Vector Store. It specifically handles `VectorStoreObservationContext` objects and extracts the text from the documents returned in the query response.','This class is part of the Spring AI observability framework and works with `VectorStore` components. It utilizes `VectorStoreObservationContext` to access query results and logs them using `LoggerFactory`. It integrates with Micrometer for observation and logging, and is used to provide insights into Vector Store operations.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.observation.VectorStoreQueryResponseObservationHandler','Implement this handler to log the content of Vector Store query responses.  Ensure the `spring-boot-starter-actuator` dependency is included for observability features. Configure logging levels to control the verbosity of the logged responses. The handler is automatically used when a `VectorStore` is observed.','51f0dabc-a045-4ff4-9ca3-db513b8dd8cf'),
('This class is a base listener for the `FiltersListener` interface, providing empty implementations for all its methods. It serves as a convenient starting point for creating custom listeners that only need to handle a specific subset of filter events.','This class is related to the `FiltersListener` interface and the `FiltersParser` generated by ANTLR4. It\'s used to listen for and react to events during the parsing of filter expressions, which are used to filter documents based on their metadata. The documentation mentions `Filter.Expression` which this class helps to process.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.FiltersBaseListener','Extend `FiltersBaseListener` to create a custom listener and override only the methods corresponding to the filter expression rules you are interested in. This avoids the need to implement all methods of the `FiltersListener` interface. For example, you might extend this class to handle only `enterCompareExpression` and `exitCompareExpression` if you are only interested in comparison operations within the filter expression.','cc7da4a0-022d-4ae7-8a91-dbeb2adfa71b'),
('This class, `SimpleVectorStoreFilterExpressionConverter`, converts `Filter.Expression` objects into SpEL (Spring Expression Language) metadata filter expressions. It\'s designed to translate filter criteria into a format suitable for querying vector stores, enabling efficient data retrieval based on metadata.','This class extends `AbstractFilterExpressionConverter` and is likely part of a larger system for interacting with vector stores. It interacts with `Filter` objects (presumably defining filter criteria) and potentially other components responsible for vector store operations. It leverages `DateTimeFormatter` for date formatting.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.converter.SimpleVectorStoreFilterExpressionConverter','The primary use case is converting filter expressions into SpEL format for querying vector stores.  For example, to convert a filter expression with date and string values, the converter handles formatting dates to a specific pattern (\'yyyy-MM-dd\\\'T\\\'HH:mm:ss\\\'Z\\\'\') and properly quoting string values for SpEL. It supports various comparison operators (AND, OR, EQ, LT, GT, etc.) and handles lists of values for \'in\' and \'not in\' operations.','3f218ede-0501-4876-9351-e791220b7dbc'),
('AbstractVectorStoreBuilder is an abstract base class for building VectorStore instances. It provides default implementations for observation-related settings and enforces the configuration of an EmbeddingModel. It supports method chaining through a generic type parameter and provides methods for configuring observation registries, custom observation conventions, and batching strategies.','This class serves as a base class for concrete VectorStore builders like MongoDBAtlasVectorStoreBuilder, MariaDBVectorStoreBuilder, OpenSearchVectorStoreBuilder, etc. It implements the VectorStore.Builder interface and is used to configure and create VectorStore instances. It interacts with EmbeddingModel and BatchingStrategy interfaces.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.AbstractVectorStoreBuilder','Extend AbstractVectorStoreBuilder to create concrete builders for specific vector stores. Implement the necessary configuration options for the target vector store within the subclass. Use the fluent API (e.g., observationRegistry(), customObservationConvention(), batchingStrategy()) to configure the builder and then build() to create the VectorStore instance. Ensure an EmbeddingModel is provided during construction.','0032ab23-2d0d-492b-882f-e8a25c81d321'),
('This class, `SimpleVectorStoreContent`, is designed to encapsulate content (text, metadata, and embedding) for use in a vector store. It provides a way to create a `Document` object from this content, which is likely used for similarity searches and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) applications.','This class is a core component for interacting with various vector stores (MongoDBAtlasVectorStore, MariaDBVectorStore, OpenSearchVectorStore, etc.) within the Spring AI project. It acts as a data transfer object (DTO) to represent the content that will be stored and retrieved from these vector stores. It\'s used in conjunction with interfaces like `VectorStore` and `VectorStoreRetriever` to perform vector-based searches.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.SimpleVectorStoreSimilarityTests','The primary use case is to create instances of `SimpleVectorStoreContent` with text, metadata, and a numerical embedding, then convert it into a `Document` object. The tests demonstrate creating content, validating its properties, and ensuring metadata immutability. It\'s important to provide a non-null and non-empty ID and embedding vector when creating an instance. The `toDocument()` method is used to create a `Document` object with a specified score.','a297b588-3b12-4c57-bf98-ebb6f1772047'),
('The `ExpressionType` enum defines the types of filter expressions that can be used to query and filter data. It supports logical operations (AND, OR, NOT), comparison operations (EQ, NE, GT, GTE, LT, LTE), and inclusion/exclusion operations (IN, NIN).','This enum is used by the `Filter.Expression` class to represent the type of expression being evaluated. It\'s also used within the `SearchRequest` class to define filter criteria for similarity searches in vector stores. It interacts with vector store implementations like `MongoDBAtlasVectorStore`, `OracleVectorStore`, and `Weaviate VectorStore` to filter data based on metadata.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.ExpressionType','The `ExpressionType` enum is primarily used to construct filter expressions for querying vector stores. For example, to filter documents where `docId` equals \'AIML-001\' and `version` equals \'1.0\', you would create a nested `Filter.Expression` using `AND`, `EQ`, `Filter.Key`, and `Filter.Value`. Alternatively, string-based filter expressions can be used directly with the `filterExpression` parameter in `SearchRequest` or the `delete` method of a vector store.','4a5631ed-bf7a-45e3-9497-f14eb4daa5b6'),
('This class is a static inner Builder class for the `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor`. It provides a fluent API to configure various components of the advisor, such as query transformers, query expander, document retriever, document joiner, document post-processors, query augmenter, task executor, scheduler, and execution order.','The `Builder` class is tightly coupled with the `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` class. It\'s used to construct instances of `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` with specific configurations. It interacts with interfaces like `QueryTransformer`, `QueryExpander`, `DocumentRetriever`, `DocumentJoiner`, `DocumentPostProcessor`, `QueryAugmenter`, `TaskExecutor`, and `Scheduler`. It\'s part of the `spring-ai-rag` module, which provides a framework for Retrieval Augmented Generation pipelines.','org.springframework.ai.rag.advisor.Builder','The Builder pattern is used to create a `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` instance with a specific configuration.  You chain method calls to set the desired components and their order. For example:\n\n```java\nRetrievalAugmentationAdvisor advisor = RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor.builder()\n    .queryTransformers(List.of(transformer1, transformer2))\n    .documentRetriever(retriever)\n    .build();\n```\n\nThis allows for flexible and configurable RAG pipelines.','bb093490-a93b-46a5-a517-f7daaee423c7'),
('This class, `BooleanExpressionContext`, is a parser rule context generated by ANTLR4, specifically for handling boolean expressions within a filter DSL. It\'s part of the system for filtering documents based on their metadata.','This class is related to the `Filter.Expression` class and the external DSL built on ANTLR4 that parses filter expressions. It\'s used in conjunction with the `similaritySearch` methods of a vector database to filter documents based on metadata key-value pairs.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.antlr4.BooleanExpressionContext','This class is not directly instantiated or used by developers. It\'s an internal component of the ANTLR4-based filter expression parser. Developers interact with the filter functionality by providing filter expressions as strings (e.g., `country == \'UK\' && year >= 2020 && isActive == true`) which are then parsed using this context.','0e0e7bff-a7a2-42d4-ae44-fd6af214272d'),
('The `Expression` record represents a boolean expression used for filtering data, particularly within the context of vector databases. It defines an expression type and two operands, allowing for comparisons, logical operations (AND/OR), and inclusion checks. It implements the `Operand` interface.','This class is central to the filtering mechanism used in `SearchRequest` and `VectorStoreDocumentRetriever`. It\'s used to define metadata filters for vector store searches. It interacts with `FilterExpressionBuilder` for programmatic construction and can be represented as a string for direct use in text-based filter expressions. It\'s also used by various vector store implementations (CassandraVectorStore, ChromaVectorStore, Milvus, OracleVectorStore) to translate filter expressions into their specific query formats.','org.springframework.ai.vectorstore.filter.Expression','The primary use case is to create filter expressions for refining vector store searches.  You can build expressions programmatically using `FilterExpressionBuilder`:\n\n```java\nFilterExpressionBuilder b = new FilterExpressionBuilder();\nExpression expression = b.eq(\"country\", \"BG\").build();\n```\n\nOr, you can use string-based expressions directly within a `SearchRequest`:\n\n```java\nvectorStore.similaritySearch(\n    SearchRequest.builder()\n    .query(\"The World\")\n    .filterExpression(\"author in [\'john\', \'jill\'] && article_type == \'blog\'\").build());\n```\n\nExpressions can be combined using AND, OR, and other operators (EQUALS, GT, LT, IN, NIN, NOT).','f6cc481d-3545-41c1-af13-fe6ad8f73a1d');
